title: skillet spaghetti
directions: In Dutch oven or a large pot, brown first 4 ingredients.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Stir in spaghetti.
Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes or until spaghetti is tender. Add the tomatoes and ketchup.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for a while on low heat to blend the flavors.
Serves 8. This is very good and may be doubled to serve larger groups.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt cake pan.
Tear biscuits in half.
Dip in butter, then brown sugar.
Place in pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground meat. Add taco seasoning according to directions. Layer meat, bean dip and cheese dip in ovenproof bowl or casserole dish.
Warm in a 350° oven until meat is warm and cheese is melted.
Remove from oven and chill slightly.

title: pretzel strawberry salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, butter and 4 tablespoons sugar and put in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together the cream cheese and 1 cup sugar; fold in whipped cream. Spread over cooled pretzel mixture.
Prepare gelatin using 1 3/4 cups boiling water.
Stir gelatin mixture into frozen strawberries.
Pour on top of cream layer and refrigerate until firm.

title: little spain's crumbly apple pie
directions: Mix the first four ingredients in mixing bowl; arrange in pie shell.
Blend brown sugar and flour and cut in margarine with pastry blender until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° on bottom shelf for 35 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Be careful of your selection.
Do not choose too young.
When once selected, give your entire thought to preparation for domestic use.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, others are constantly getting them in hot water.
This makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with love and seasoned with kisses.
Wrap them in a mantle of charity, keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
Thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: apricot meringue bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Blend butter or margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and egg yolks together. Work in flour.
Lightly flour hands.
Pat mixture into baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread evenly with preserves.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually beat in 1/3 cup sugar.
Continue beating until meringue forms stiff, glossy peaks.
Fold in nuts.
Spread over preserves.
Return to oven. Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Serves 16.

title: oatmeal party cookies
directions: Mix margarine, powdered sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add flour and oatmeal.
On an ungreased cookie sheet, drop teaspoonful in ball.
Flatten.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Dip cookies in melted chocolate and nuts.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Cream butter, sugar, spices and eggs; mix well.
Keep mix in freezer.

title: chili-cheese franks
directions: In large saucepan, combine chili with beans, cheese soup and onions.
Add franks; heat to boiling.
Simmer mixture about 5 minutes to blend flavors.
To serve, place a frank on each toasted bun.
Top each with chili cheese sauce and sprinkle with crushed corn chips.
Yield:
8 to 10 sandwiches.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain, spread out in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with sour cream, then Mozzarella cheese.
Cook meat in skillet until color disappears.
Add tomato sauce plus the package of spices found in spaghetti box and a small amount of salt.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over layered spaghetti.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese found in spaghetti box.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread pieces in milk for 5 minutes.
Add butter, salt, sugar and raisins.
Pour slightly beaten eggs over bread mixture. Add vanilla and mix well.

title: stuffed peach salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Fill peach halves and serve on lettuce.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients; fold in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
This is a very delicious dip.
Use with crackers or fresh vegetables.
A hit at any party!

title: raisin peanut balls
directions: Plump raisins by steaming.
Drain and chop.
Roll coconut into fine pieces.
Toast to a light brown in moderate oven (370°).

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers thin and cover with a little salt.
Let stand for 1/2 hour.
Drain off any liquid that has formed.
Dice green onions into cucumbers.

title: herbed cheese with garlic and lemon
directions: With electric mixer, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add remaining ingredients except lemon peel.
Mix well. Stir in peel. Cover and chill several hours.
Serve as a spread with assorted crackers and/or fruit.
Makes 1 cup.

title: potato salad(100 servings)
directions: Peel and block potatoes.
Boil until tender.
Chop celery, pickles, onions and peppers.
Add to potatoes; stir slightly.
Add mayonnaise and eggs (chopped) last.

title: low calorie applesauce cookies
directions: Cream butter, egg, applesauce and Sugar Twin.
Mix flour, spices and sour milk, then combine with creamed mixture until well blended.
Add nuts and raisins.
Place by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Stir together and boil until hard crack stage on medium heat. (Use a candy thermometer.)
Then add red food coloring, 2 tablespoons butter, 1 teaspoon cinnamon oil (more if you like it hotter).
Mix well.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
After it hardens (about 1 hour), break up.
Put in bowl or jar with powdered sugar and shake until candy is well coated.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onions, butter, bell peppers, celery and green onions until wilted.
Add meats, soups, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Heat to a slight boil.
Add tomatoes and chilies, parsley and rice.
Pour into oblong 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake, tightly covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir after 30 minutes.

title: peachy pecan bread
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Finely chop 1 cup peaches.
In blender combine remaining peaches, oleo, eggs, reserved peach juice and lemon juice.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Add egg mixture; stir until moistened.
Fold in reserved peaches and nuts.
Bake in a greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Spread with peach preserves.
Cool in pan at least 10 minutes.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain.
Stir in catsup and chili powder.
Puree beans in blender, then stir them in ground chuck. Heat through.
Keep warm in fondue pot or chafing dish.
Layer with cheese.
Serve with Fritos or Tostitos tortilla chips.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix salmon with first 6 ingredients.
Chill several hours. Combine nuts and parsley flakes, shape into log and roll in nuts and parsley.
Chill.

title: cheddar garlic dip
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature and beat well. Refrigerate.
Keeps well.
It's great for using during the holidays or for parties.

title: cabbage slaw with yogurt dressing
directions: Shred cabbage about 1/4-inch thick; put in bowl.
Trim ends and tops of radishes.
Slice and add to cabbage.
Fold in the yogurt.
Taste.
Add sugar and salt, if desired.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately.
Good served with barbecued meats or fish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a large 6-quart saucepot in hot oil, brown roast on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover; cook 45 minutes or until roast and vegetables are fork-tender.
Remove roast and vegies.
Stir together flour and remaining 1/4 cup water until smooth.
Gradually stir into soup mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Garnish with fresh parsley if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: the next best thing to robert redford french silk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool and layer the following ingredients.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Combine macaroni and remaining ingredients. Toss lightly but thoroughly.
Chill.

title: quick golden pound cake
directions: Pour water, oil and eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients to this.
Mix for 4 minutes, until very well mixed.
Pour into tube pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes, or until done.

title: ooey gooey cake
directions: Bake at 350° until done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Combine soup and mushrooms.
Toss beans with mixture.
Top with fried onions and crumbled bacon.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Add soda to boiling water and cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and soda mixture.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well (this takes a very large pan for mixing).
Keep mixture in tight container in refrigerator.
Let set at least 8 hours before using from it.
May be kept 6 weeks.

title: faye's french coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat eggs until fluffy. Add sugar, vanilla, buttermilk, butter and coconut.
Mix thoroughly and pour into pie shell.
Bake until golden brown (about 45 minutes).

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with pineapple and juice.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Cut oleo over cake and sprinkle nuts and coconut.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix package of Jell-O and boiling water together; stir well. Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator and chill.
Will keep for several days.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, milk and flavoring.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding mix for two (2) minutes with electric mixer until thick.
Then add sour cream and stir in until smooth. Then add Cool Whip.
And also stir until creamy and smooth.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas, adding pudding mixture between each layer.
Top with vanilla wafers.

title: doo-doo drops
directions: Melt chips over medium heat until smooth in a large pot, stirring continuously to avoid scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in peanuts and chow mein noodles until coated.
Finally, stir in marshmallows until coated.
Spoon drops onto wax paper, about 3 inches in diameter.
Refrigerate until solid.
Makes 20 to 24.

title: chicken wings
directions: Marinate the chicken wings in the sauce for 2 hours.
Bake in marinade sauce for 2 hours at 325°.
Turn chicken while it is baking.
Sprinkle garlic powder over wings after they have been drained and serve hot.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover; bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: beef-noodle bake
directions: Brown ground beef in 2 tablespoons fat.
Add other ingredients and simmer until heated through.
Mix thoroughly with noodles, cooked according to package directions.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in a 400° oven.
Do not let cook dry.
Strips of Cheddar cheese may be laid on top before baking if desired.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: In a large bowl, stir with fork the flour, sugar and salt. Cut in shortening until crumbly.
In small bowl, beat together water, egg and vinegar.
Add to flour mixture until well moistened.
Divide dough into 5 portions and shape each in a flat round patty, ready for rolling.
Wrap in plastic or waxed paper and chill.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; add water and lemon juice.
Over high heat, bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cook, stirring occasionally until slightly thick and clear, approximately 4 to 5 minutes.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved. Chill until thickened but not set, about 1 hour.
Stir in strawberries.
Spoon into baked pastry shell.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.

title: creamy persimmon fudge
directions: Combine ingredients in order given and cook to a very firm ball when dropped into ice water.
Then add butter when mixture is cool.
Beat until it begins to take on a dull appearance. Pour in buttered pan. Nuts are optional.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough salad dressing (or mayonnaise) to make mixture moist.
Garnish with slices of hard-boiled eggs and paprika.
Cover and refrigerate until cool.

title: tomato marmalade
directions: Pour boiling water on tomatoes.
To remove skins, cut up and cover with vinegar.
Let stand overnight, then pour off vinegar. Rinse 2 or 3 times.
Add to pulp an equal amount of sugar.
Add thinly sliced lemon, rind included.
Add 1 sliced orange.
Boil until thick like marmalade, 220° on thermometer at least 1 hour. Use spoon sheeting test.
Pour in hot jars and seal with wax.

title: chin-chin
directions: Rub in the butter or margarine to the flour.
Add baking soda and mix thoroughly.
Whisk together the nutmeg, eggs, sugar and salt and add to the flour.
Mix together and add water.
Knead well and cover.
Leave for about 10 minutes for flour to rise if self-rising flour is not being used.
Spread the pastry flat thin on a level board or table top, using a rolling pin.

Cut into squares or triangular shapes (small, bite size pieces) and spread a little flour over them to stop them from sticking together. Deep fry in vegetable oil until golden brown and drain off oil by placing on absorbent paper.
Serve as snacks with your favorite drink.

title: dad's shrimp and crab salad
directions: Mix together with salad dressing and 1/2 cup dill pickle juice.
The more salad dressing, the more moist it is.
Use your judgment on this one.

title: english muffin breakfast treat
directions: Split muffins and toast lightly.
Blend marmalade and butter. Slice banana and fold into marmalade mixture.
Spoon onto muffins and broil 1 to 3 minutes until bubbly.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chili cheesers
directions: Butter a 8 or 9-inch pan.
Put chili peppers on bottom of dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Mix milk and eggs and pour over top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Stir together flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle one side of meat with half the flour mixture; pound in.
Turn meat and pound in remaining flour mixture.
Cut meat into 6 serving pieces.
Melt shortening in large skillet; brown meat over medium heat about 15 minutes.
Cover tightly; simmer 1 hour.
Add small amount of water if necessary.

title: chocolate chip treasure cookies
directions: Heat oven 350° to 375°.
In small bowl, mix graham cracker crumbs, flour and baking powder.
In large mixer bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk and margarine until smooth.
Add graham cracker crumb mixture; mix well.
Stir in coconut, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded tbsp. onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
(Makes about 3 dozen.)

title: gram gehris' tossed salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: chicken oliver
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Line a greased casserole pan with dried beef slices.
Wrap each breast half with a slice of bacon.
Place breast in a single layer in the lined pan.
Mix together in a bowl the sour cream and mushroom soup.
Pour over the chicken and bake, uncovered.

title: blueberry jello
directions: Mix the Jell-O with the boiling water.
Mix well. Add the blueberries with juice and the pineapple with juice.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan until set.
Mix the sour cream and sugar. Spread over Jell-O.
Cover with sliced toasted almonds.

title: angie's suicide drink
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large cup. Stir well. Have fun!

title: jack's baked macaroni
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. Melt butter and blend flour and seasonings into it.

Gradually add milk and onion and cook, stirring until thickened. Turn burner off and add cheese. Stir until melted. Put macaroni and cheese mixture in a 9 x 13 inch casserole pan. Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine remaining sugar, nuts and cinnamon. Grease and flour 9-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Spoon half the batter into pan.
Sprinkle 1/3 nut mixture over.
Add remaining batter. Sprinkle remaining nut mixture on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Cool after baking 20 minutes in pan.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Mix lemon juice, jelly and ketchup in saucepan or crock-pot. While sauce is cooking, mix ground chuck, egg, onion, seasoned salt, milk and oatmeal together.
Form into 1-inch balls and brown in skillet.
Drain and put with sauce and simmer for at least 1/2 hour.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix in order given.
Mold into small rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Slice and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: low calorie chocolate dessert
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, cover bottom with graham crackers.
Mix Jell-O pudding and milk; fold in chocolate Cool Whip.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture over crackers.
Put another layer of crackers, and top with remaining Jell-O mixture.
Top with tub of regular Cool Whip.

title: mint brownie bites
directions: In a small saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat and cool completely. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: joanne's jello pie
directions: *Suggested fruits:

1 cup diced, peeled and pitted fresh peaches or apricots; 1 cup fresh raspberries or blueberries; 1 cup diced orange sections or fresh strawberries; 1 (8 3/4 ounce) can apricots or sliced peaches, drained or diced; or 1 (8 3/4 ounce) can fruit cocktail, drained.

title: pecan chocolate fudge deluxe
directions: Into a heavy, wide mouthed saucepan, put sugar, evaporated milk, a pinch of salt, butter, chocolate and cocoa.
Cook over low heat until the sugar melts, then over a medium flame until the mixture thickens and heavily clings to the spoon.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Let stand a few minutes, then beat until the gloss is gone from the candy.
Stir in 1 cup of pecans.
Pour in buttered pan and cut into squares.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage in skillet on top of stove.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 10-inch pie plate, place browned, drained sausage. Top with hash browns, then sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and pepper.
Pour over Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
(Can be cooled, refrigerated and reheated.) Serves 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together using only 1 cup croutons.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put 1/2 cup croutons on top and dribble 1 stick of melted oleo or butter over this.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops of each pepper off, remove seeds and membranes and rinse.
Cook peppers in boiling water (enough to cover them) for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Brown hamburger with onion; drain excess oil. Add salt, garlic salt, rice and 1 cup tomato sauce; heat through. Stuff each pepper with mixture, placing peppers in ungreased baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over peppers.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover, cook 15 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Prepare lime, orange, cherry and grape gelatins using 1 1/4 cups water per package.
Let set in separate pans 1/4-inch thick. Cut into 1/4-inch squares when set.

title: amaretto cherry-cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese until smooth and fluffy.
Beat in almond filling, eggs, salt, liqueur and almond extract until mixture is well blended.
Pour mixture into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in center of oven for 10 minutes.
Blend sugar and 2 tablespoons of the almonds in a cup.
Sprinkle over top of pie. Continue baking 30 minutes longer or until pie is puffed and golden (will sink as it cools).
Remove pie to wire rack; cool.
Spoon cherry pie filling over baked pie; top with remaining almonds.

title: old-fashioned carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Blend well and add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake about 1 hour at 325°.
Do not overbake.

title: lemon garlic chicken
directions: Set oven to 350°.
In one bowl, beat the egg.
In second bowl combine flour and garlic powder.
Melt the butter in the skillet on medium heat.
Dip each piece of chicken in the egg, then in the flour mixture.
Brown the coated chicken in the skillet.
When the chicken has browned lightly, bake it in the oven for another 15 minutes (or until fully cooked).
While chicken is baking, cut the lemon in half.
Reserve one half for garnish and squeeze the juice from the other half into the skillet.
Dissolve the bouillon in hot water and pour in skillet.
Simmer gently for a few minutes to make sure the bouillon and lemon have mixed thoroughly.
When the chicken is done, place on plate over rice or buttered noodles, then drizzle the sauce over the chicken and garnish with a slice of lemon.
Serves 4.

title: audrey's favorite vegetable dip
directions: In small bowl, add ingredients (except vegetables) and mix well.
Chill and serve with fresh, raw vegetables.
Great dip for parties!

title: shrimp mold
directions: Melt cheese and soup together.
Add other ingredients.
Add gelatine last.
Pour into mold greased with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with paprika after unmolding on lettuce.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy ham stir-fry
directions: Pour oil into preheated nonstick skillet; add celery, onion and green pepper.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes or until vegetables are tender and crisp.
Add ham, garlic powder and pepper and stir-fry another 3 or 4 minutes.
Add rice and stir-fry until hot.
Stir in bacon and soy sauce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix first four ingredients together so flour won't lump.
Add enough water to make a paste.
Add milk. (Add more if it remains too thick after cooking.)
Put on medium heat.
Boil until it thickens.
Stir consistently or it will stick.
Great over pancakes or hot biscuits.

title: beef and "tater" bake
directions: Pat meat into an 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; drain.
Combine mashed potatoes and 3/4 cup cheese; spread on meat.
Top with remainder of cheese. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Mix 2 cans soup, water and milk together.
Brown hamburger with onion.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low all day.
Grate cheese on top before serving.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and chill.

title: cheese tuna fish sandwich
directions: Mix the tuna, eggs, olives and mayonnaise together.
Spread 2 slices of bread with tuna mixture.
Top with third slice.
Frost top and sides.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Grease pan. Over medium heat melt together Karo, sugar and peanut butter, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture over Rice Krispies until cereal is well coated.
Press in pan.
Cut in squares before completely cooled.

title: quiche
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; then drain. Combine remaining ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 375° or when knife inserted comes out clean.

title: cookies and cream cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine; press into 9-inch spring-form pan. Cream the cream cheese and sugar; fold in whipped cream and cookies.
Pour into pan and place in the freezer.
Bring 1/2 cup cream to a simmer; add chocolate and stir until smooth.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour over cheesecake and smooth top.
Store in freezer. Set out 15 minutes before serving.
It freezes really well if you cover it.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: sugarless ice cream(5 quart freezer)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a blender and blend well.
Pour into a 5 quart freezer can.
Add enough water or skim milk to fill can to the fill line.
Freeze.

title: classic lemon curd
directions: In a saucepan, lightly beat the egg and egg yolks.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat; stir constantly until the mixture thickens, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve hot or cold. Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: gooey marshmallow treats
directions: Pop popcorn.
Melt bag of marshmallows on low heat until all melted.
Mix marshmallows and popcorn together in a big bowl. Then spray a pan with vegetable spray.
Press popcorn in the pan. Freeze for 5 minutes.
Top with cinnamon.
You may add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla to marshmallow mix before adding popcorn.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put whole drained strawberries in pie shell. Boil other ingredients for 3 minutes, stirring. Let cool, then pour over strawberries. Top with Cool Whip. Serve chilled.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain.
Mix all other ingredients together with squash.
Place in a greased baking pan.
Cook casserole about 30 or 40 minutes, or until golden brown on top in a 350° oven.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Season well.
Add mushroom stems and pieces to hamburger.
Clean and boil potatoes.
Mash and season potatoes. In 9 x 13-inch baking dish (greased), put the hamburger/mushroom mixture.
Make another layer by combining whole corn and creamed corn.
The top layer is the mashed potatoes.
Dot with butter after spreading over corn.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving!

title: taco chip dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain well.
Stir in tomatoes and taco seasoning.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine cheeses.
Layer meat mixture and cheeses in shallow baking dish.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes or until cheeses are melted.
Serve hot with taco chips.

title: southern buttermilk corn bread
directions: Preheat an 8 or 10-inch iron skillet in 425° oven or grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 425°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna or swordfish with tomato-arugula salsa
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Cut fish into serving size pieces.
For salsa, in a medium size bowl combine tomatoes, pepper, arugula or basil, green onion and 2 tablespoons dressing.
Spray unheated rack of broiling pan with nonstick spray.
Place fish or rack and brush with some of the dressing.
Broil 4-inches from heat until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Allow 4 to 6 minutes per 1/2-inch thickness of fish.
Turn fish once and brush with remaining dressing.
Transfer fish to serving plates and spoon salsa over each.
Garnish with additional arugula and lemon if desired. Serves 4.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and add onion, salt, pepper and garlic, then add tomato paste and water.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and let simmer about 30 minutes.
Boil noodles.
Mix cheese, eggs and parsley together.
Layer 1/2 of noodles and 1/2 hamburger mix, then 1/2 cheese.
Then the other 1/2 of noodles, hamburger mix and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pie #2
directions: Layer chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix broth, flour and water.
Stir until smooth and thickened.
Slice boiled eggs over chicken.
Pour broth over eggs and chicken.
Pour pastry for top over chicken mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: vegetable corn muffins
directions: Grease pans.
Mix the first 7 ingredients.
Melt margarine or butter.
Stir in eggs and milk.
Combine with flour.
Stir just until flour mixture is moistened.
Quickly pour batter into pan. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add all ingredients except dressing. Mix and pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup Pepperidge Farm dressing over top.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and drizzle over dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break up cauliflower. Drain olives; chop onions. Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Chill at least 3 hours.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: delicious baked beans
directions: Place in crock-pot and cook all day on low.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off fruit.
Use 3 cups of juice to cook with pudding and tapioca. Cool and mix with fruit. Chill and serve.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Chop orange slices, dates and nuts; with coconut, add to melted margarine.
Let stand.

title: city chicken
directions: Put the pork and veal on sticks alternately until 3/4 filled. Take the eggs and beat well in shallow bowl. Dip each stick, then roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in oil until browned.
Put in roasting pan.
Pour a mixture of the soup, milk and mushrooms, mixed well, over the City Chicken in the roaster. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tom's tuna cakes
directions: Chop the tuna, then mix all the ingredients, except the bread crumbs and oil, together.
Form patties.
Dip each patty in the bread crumbs and fry in hot oil.
Serve with macaroni and cheese or soup.

title: ham and cheese brunch
directions: Cover bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan with half the bread cubes.
Layer broccoli, ham and cheese over bread.
Top with remaining bread cubes.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and seasonings and pour over casserole.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° until tests done (knife inserted in center comes clean), 55 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 8 good servings.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: In electric skillet, saute onion in oil.
Mix together all ingredients except chicken.
Pour into skillet and simmer for 5 minutes.
Put chicken in skillet and cover.
Stir sauce and turn chicken occasionally.
Cooking time is approximately 45 minutes or until chicken is done.
(This recipe is excellent for Sloppy Joes as well as with pork steak.)

title: easy bean soup
directions: Blend cold water, flour and sour cream until smooth.
Pour into soup.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: blueberry cheesecake delight
directions: Mix together crackers, butter and sugar.
Press into bottom of an 8 x 10-inch baking pan.
To the eggs, add 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Mix until smooth.
Spread over graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Chill.
Top with pie filling and whipped cream.

title: barbeque sauce
directions: To blend spices with tomatoes, add to juice, simmer for 10 minutes, after which is ready for use.

title: new york style cheese cake
directions: In medium bowl combine graham crackers, melted butter and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Spray sides with cooking spray.
In large bowl combine flour, cornstarch and yogurt; add cream cheese, beat well.
Beat in next 4 ingredients plus 1 cup sugar until smooth. Pour over crust. Bake 5 minutes in 375° oven.
Reduce temperature to 300° and bake 45 minutes.
Turn off oven, cool cake in oven 30 minutes.
In small bowl blend sour cream with 2 tablespoons sugar; spread over top.
Return to oven until set.
Chill before serving.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in 8-inch square microproof container.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 6 minutes.
Rotate dish a half turn.
Microwave for 4 to 6 minutes longer or until peaches are tender.
Serve with ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ultra-light chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Oil cookie sheets well and combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Combine egg, water and vanilla.
Set aside.
Combine and blend brown sugar and Crisco at low speed on mixer.
Add egg mixture.
Beat until well mixed.
Add flour mixture slowly while mixing.
Stir in chocolate bits.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate with water until melted; set aside.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
Beat butter until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Beat well after each until smooth.
Stir in chocolate and vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk beating until smooth. Beat egg whites in separate bowl until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans lined with wax papper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove to cake rack.
Fill with Coconut-Pecan Filling. Frost sides and edge with Chocolate Butter Cream.

title: fried chicken
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water for 20 minutes. Mix pancake mix and water together. Coat chicken pieces in pancake batter. Cook chicken in deep fat until brown or about 5 minutes per side.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the oleo, Crisco and sugar well (take oleo out of refrigerator when ready to use). Add vanilla (to taste).
Add milk and flour, which has been sifted with cocoa, alternately.
Pour into steple pan which has been greased and floured.
Cook 2 hours at 275°.
Ice with favorite icing.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heavily butter 8 custard cups.
Place on baking sheet for easy handling.
Slide into hot oven while mixing batter.
All ingredients can be mixed in blender.
Milk and eggs should be at least 75° to 80° (room temperature).
Pour into heated custard cups, filling each 1/2 full to allow room for popping. Bake in hot oven at 425° for 20 minutes, or until popped, crisp and golden.
Reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes longer.

title: taco soup
directions: Fry hamburg and onion; drain.
Drain hominy, pinto beans, lima beans and kidney beans.
Combine all ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve as soup.
Good with fine shredded cheese on top.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil in large bowl with wooden spoon.
Add eggs one at a time and beat in.
Blend in flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and vanilla, then add apples, coconut and nuts.
Stir until well blended.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt or tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in an electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: japanese chicken salad
directions: Make the dressing 1 day ahead and refrigerate.

title: chili bean baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Wrap each thigh with 1 bacon slice; secure with toothpick.
Combine in baking dish rice, water, beans and broccoli.
Top with chicken.
Cover with foil; bake 30 minutes.
Uncover, bake about 20 minutes longer or until chicken is no longer pink when cut into.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes, until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie
roll
in
pizza pan or 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in oven
at
for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese
and sugar.
Spread mixture on top of sugar cookie. Mix strawberries and glaze together. Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Chill.
Before
serving, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: granny pack's stack cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar until light. Stir in molasses.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add to creamed mixture along with milk, beating after each.
Stir together flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture along with milk, beating after each. Grease and flour 3 round pans.
Pour 1 1/3 cups batter into each. Bake at 375° until done.
Remove from oven and cool on a rack. Repeat until batter is used.
Put applesauce between each layer and on top.
Refrigerate.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour, dry yeast, sugar and soda together, then cut in Crisco and add buttermilk.
Mix well.
Turn out on floured board and knead enough to harden together and becomes smooth.
Place in greased bowl and rub top of mixture with oil.
Cover loosely.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage-sauerkraut dinner
directions: Mix well sauerkraut, onion, sugar and caraway seed; set aside. In greased 3-quart casserole, layer the potatoes, half the sauerkraut mixture.
Add wine.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Can cook in layers in crock-pot (6 to 8 hours).

title: basic recipe
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with fruit.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: In medium bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with vegetables.

title: corn flake peanut butter balls
directions: Cook sugar and Karo syrup until sugar melts.
Turn off and add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Stir in corn flakes.
Roll into balls. Place on wax paper.

title: homemade popsicles
directions: Dissolve gelatin and Kool-Aid with sugar in hot water.
Add cold water.
Pour into molds.
Freeze.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, egg, and 1 stick butter well.
Press into 11 x 14-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Beat until fluffy.
Pour over cake mixture.
Cover with chopped pecans.
Bake 55 minutes at 300°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: white salad
directions: Add baking soda and sugar to egg whites.
Fold in Ritz crackers and nuts.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: basic baked beans
directions: Day before serving, soak beans in cold water, covered, overnight (water should cover beans completely).
Next day, drain beans in colander; rinse under cold water.
Turn into a 6-quart kettle.
Cover with 5 cups of water.
Add onion, bay leaves, lite salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, or until beans are tender.
Add more water if needed.
Remove bay leaves.
To bake, preheat oven to 350°.
Drain bean mixture, reserving liquid.
Turn beans into a 4-quart baking dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Combine ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire and mustard; mix well.
Pour over beans; stir to combine.
Add enough of the reserved liquid to cover the beans.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over medium heat until it boils; boil 5 minutes.
Pop 4 quarts popcorn.
Pour over corn in large shallow pan.
Put in 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Pour out on greased waxed paper; cool.
Put in Ziploc bags.

title: marie's raw vegetable dip
directions: Heat tomato soup, Jell-O, cream cheese and water until melted. Beat until smooth, then add green pepper, pecans, onion and salad dressing.
Chill and serve with raw vegetables.

title: christmas ice cream
directions: Soften the ice cream in a large bowl.
Crush macaroons and stir into ice cream.
Add remaining items and mix well.
Place in refrigerator trays and freeze.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in a skillet.
Add brown sugar and cook over medium high heat until the sugar is dissolved.
Remove the pan from the heat and place slices of pineapple in a layer over the caramel.
Sprinkle with pecan halves.
Place a cherry in the center of each pineapple slice.
Sift together the cake flour and baking powder.
Beat the egg yolks in a separate bowl.
Add the melted butter and vanilla to the egg yolks.
Sift the sugar in a separate bowl.
Whip the egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Fold in the sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Then fold in the yolk mixture and finally the flour mixture, 1/4 cup at a time.
(If using a cake mix, substitute the pineapple juice for the water in the mix.)

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy.
Flavor with love and kindly service, fold in 4 cups of prayers and faith. Blend well.
Fold in daily life.
Bake well with the warmth of human kindness to serve with a smile any time, it will satisfy the hunger of starved souls.

title: delicious "bloody marys" are different
directions: Put ice cubes in 1 1/2-quart container.
Add next 15 ingredients, one at a time, and stir after each. Serve over 2 cubes each in 8 ounce glasses.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with cleaned, cooked and chilled shrimp.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Marinate shrimp 1 hour in this mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cauliflower and shrimp dish
directions: Cook fresh or frozen cauliflower until tender.
Drain.

title: old fashioned fruit salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add miniature marshmallows to hot mixture and dissolve.
Add pineapple and banana slices.
Let set in refrigerator for at least 5 or 6 hours.
Mix pineapple juice, flour, egg and sugar; cook like pudding.
Set aside and let cool.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and oleo.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Set aside the cracker and butter, and combine the rest of the ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix well. Spread mixture into a long baking dish. Cover with Ritz Cracker crumbs. Next swirl melted butter over the top of the crackers. Bake at 350° until top is brown and vegetables are done. Best if vegetables are slightly crisp. Leftovers are great and this freezes wonderfully.

title: pineapple sorbet
directions: Arrange rings on baking sheet and freeze until firm.
Cut into small pieces.
Transfer into processor and process until smooth and creamy.

title: hot mustard
directions: Combine dry mustard and vinegar.
Soak overnight.
Add sugar and eggs and cook until slightly thickened.
Place in jars and refrigerate.

title: grandma's spice cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and egg.
Add buttermilk and molasses. Mix soda, flour, nutmeg and cinnamon together and add to first mixture.
Mix until blended.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
May be served warm with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: roast apples
directions: Core and slice apples.
Cut heavy foil into 8-inch squares. Place sliced apples on squares.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, cloves and add dot of butter.
Wrap.
Roast about 45 minutes over coals.

title: japanese fruit cake pie
directions: Mix melted butter and sugar. Let cool to room temperature. Add eggs; mix thoroughly. Add vanilla, raisins, coconut and nuts. Pour into unbaked
pie shells. Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 375° oven.

title: hot rolls
directions: Add yeast to warm milk and sugar. Let stand for 5 minutes. Add salt, shortening and flour. Mix until smooth. Place dough over pan of warm water. Let rise until light (about 30 minutes). Place on board (without kneading). Pat out, then cut with cutter. Grease rolls with butter. Let rise 15 minutes. Bake at 425° until brown.

title: baked tuna-stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash potatoes.
Rub skins all over with margarine.
Prick with fork.
Bake on oven rack 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: apple walnut cobbler
directions: Place the apples in a greased 9-inch round cake pan.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 cup nuts.
Sprinkle over the apples.
Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar the baking powder and salt. In a separate bowl beat together the egg, milk and butter.
Add to the flour mixture; mix until smooth.
Pour over the apples; top with 1/4 cup nuts.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, until the top is golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: celery casserole
directions: Mix celery, soup, pimento, water chestnuts and almonds.
Top with bread crumbs and margarine.
Bake in greased casserole dish for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: moravian sugar cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Put flour, salt and sugar in a bowl and mix well.
Make well in middle of flour and pour in mashed potatoes, beaten eggs, shortening and yeast.
Mix well. Let stand for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until doubled in size.
Spread on greased pans.
Let rise.
Then sprinkle thick with brown sugar, dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° to 400° for about 20 minutes or until brown.

title: better than ice cream cake
directions: Mix and cook cake according to directions. While cake is in the oven, mix together pineapple and sugar in sauce pan. Bring to a boil then simmer until cake is done. After cake has cooled a few minutes, punch holes in top with a fork. Pour pineapple and sugar mixture over cake. Cool cake completely. Mix vanilla instant pudding as directed on box. Pour on top of cake. Top cake with Cool Whip and then sprinkle coconut on top of Cool Whip.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken in large shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over chicken and marinate at least 1 hour.
Remove from marinade.
Grill chicken over hot coals 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Turn and baste with marinade every 5 minutes.
Do not overcook!
Chicken can be baked in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes in 1/2 cup marinade, covered, and broiled 5 minutes to brown.

title: maple syrup
directions: Pit as many sour cherries as you wish to use. This must be done by pinching out the seeds with your fingers as they must have a good shape and not be torn any more than you can help. Put the pitted cherries into a bowl or crock and cover with apple cider vinegar. Cover and let stand for three days. Drain and measure the cherries. Add a cup of sugar for each cup of fruit and allow this mixture to stand for three more days. Be sure to stir it well each day so that the sugar melts completely and permeates the whole thing. Put a half stick of cinnamon into each freshly washed pint jar. Add the sugared fruit and seal. That's all: no cooking or processing of any kind.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve
1 cup warm water with yeast.	In
large
bowl mix buttermilk, oil, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add yeast mixture.
Stir in flour 1 cup at a time until dough will knead without being sticky.
Roll out and
cut
biscuits.
Let raise. Bake at 350° until brown.
Dough
can
be refrigerated for a week.

title: garden special meal
directions: Put in layers in baking dish and heat.
Also good on omelet, scrambled eggs, fish, or with soup stock.

title: super sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage meat, onion, celery or green pepper, stirring and chopping constantly until all sausage meat is broken up and vegetables are soaked with fat.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce and tomatoes; then add macaroni.
Put into a large casserole.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, oregano, basil and salt.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
In another bowl, mix cottage cheese, egg and Parmesan cheese.
Cook the lasagna noodles.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan as follows:

title: zucchini and swiss cheese
directions: Boil sliced zucchini in salted water until tender; drain. Melt butter in skillet.
Add zucchini and other ingredients.
Put cheese on top.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: light salmon mousse
directions: Put salmon in large bowl; mash with bones.
In a blender or mixer, combine yogurt and cottage cheese.
Pour into salmon.
Stir in chopped dill.
Pour salmon liquid into small pan.
Over low heat, stir in gelatin until dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Add to salmon; mix thoroughly.
Line bottom of 3 to 4-cup mold, bowl or loaf pan with dill sprigs and cucumber slices if desired.
Pour salmon mixture.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Unmold; serve with crackers. Serves 10 to 12 as appetizer.

title: hamburger, bean, potato casserole
directions: In large casserole, place a layer of approximately 1/2 potatoes, then a layer of 1 can beans and a layer of approximately 1/2 ground beef, then spread 1 can of the soup over the top. Repeat.

title: almond broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter; saute broccoli for about 20 minutes.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole; bake at 350° until hot, about 25 minutes.

title: barbecue beef on a bun
directions: Cover and roast in 300° to 325° oven for 3 to 4 hours.
Pull apart with 2 forks and serve on warm buns.

title: chocolate-pecan pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Stir in chocolate morsels and pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If desired, serve with ice cream or whipped cream. Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, and cinnamon in a large bowl. Add eggs and oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened; do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts, and bananas.
Spoon batter into three greased and floured nine inch cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove.
Cool completely.

title: broccoli-rice
directions: Add margarine to water and bring to a boil.
Add broccoli cuts and cook 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add rice.
Blend thoroughly.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz, mixing well. Add cream soup of your choice.
Make sure to blend Cheez Whiz thoroughly.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or microwave on Medium-high for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Stir
together first 5 ingredients.
Add other ingredients. Give
200 strokes.
The consistency should be soupy and stringy like
pancake
batter.
Add
3 cups whole wheat flour. Let sit
5 minutes.
Knead 10 minutes.
Rise 20 minutes.
Bake at 325° to 350°
for
to 45 minutes.
A hollow sound when thumped indicates a thoroughly baked loaf.

title: chili cornbread
directions: Combine flour, corn meal, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir in cheese, corn, chilies, milk and oil.
In small bowl beat eggs. Add to corn meal mixture and stir only until blended.
Turn into oiled 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 9 servings.

title: cherry herring
directions: Mix together and put in glass jug.
Shake this mixture every once in a while for a week.
Then let set without stirring until Thanksgiving.
Drain off the liquid and pour into wine bottle.
Eat the cherries.
Save the juice until Christmas.
Serve in tiny wine glasses as an after dinner cordial.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, sour cream, soup and poppy seed.
Pour in 2-quart casserole dish.
Crumble snack crackers and pour melted butter in small bowl.
Mix thoroughly, making sure crackers are moist.
Sprinkle crackers on top of chicken mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: ham-broccoli and potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Place potato slices into a 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Cover potato slices with boiling water and add salt.
Let stand, uncovered, for 15 minutes; drain thoroughly.
Toss the potatoes with the melted margarine and 1 egg.
Press mixture against the bottom and side of pie plate. Bake 10 minutes.

title: roy burgers
directions: Prepare dressing mix according to package directions, with oil and vinegar, substituting soy sauce for water.
For every pound of ground round, mix in 1/4 cup dressing marinade.
Form mixture into patties and grill, basting with marinade periodically.
Serve with leftover marinade.

title: swiss ham ring
directions: Heat oven.
Cook broccoli; drain and cut up into smaller pieces.
In bowl, combine flour, onion, margarine, mustard and lemon juice.
Add Swiss cheese and ham; mix.
Arrange rolls on a cookie sheet, with center being about a 3-inch circle.
Spoon filling in a ring evenly over bases of triangles.
Fold points of triangles over filling and tuck under bases of triangles. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until browned.
Serve hot.

title: unique red-eye gravy
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Add the ham and saute over medium-high heat until browned, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and stir in flour.
Continue to stir until smooth, bubbly and flour is lightly browned.
Add chicken stock, Coke and coffee, stirring frequently, until gravy is smooth and thickened (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: taco pie
directions: Press biscuits into pie pan.
Saute meat with onions, salt and pepper.
Add water, tomato paste and seasoning mix together in pan. Cook on low heat approximately 10 minutes.
Put 1/2 meat mixture on top of biscuits.
Top with 1/2 cheese.
Repeat again and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: corn pudding
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add all ingredients and mix well. Bake in greased casserole dish 30 to 35 minutes or until light brown at 350°.

title: romanian cabbage rolls(sarmale)
directions: Saute onions; add 2 teaspoons salt and paprika.
Add onion mixture to raw meat and rice.
Add the last teaspoon of salt.
If you have the Hungarian spice vegeta, add some of that; if not you will need to add more salt.
Add water, pepper and dill weed leaves.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Mix 1/3 cup sugar, cornstarch and pineapple.
Cook over low heat until mixture is thick and clear.
Soften cream cheese at room temperature and blend with 1/2 cup sugar, milk, eggs and vanilla. Pour pineapple mixture in pastry shell.
Pour cream cheese mixture on top.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake for 50 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: barbecue flank steak
directions: For the marinade, mix together the first five ingredients. Pour over and marinate steak for 4 hours or longer, turning often. Drain and barbecue over glowing coals, about 5 minutes on each side for medium.
Slice meat on diagonal (more tender) into thin slices to serve.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Bring milk, cocoa, butter and sugar to a rolling boil.
Then boil for 1 full minute.
Remove from heat and mix in oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper and allow to cool.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips on low heat.
Add milk.
Stir until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Let set until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 stick margarine and cheese.
Put into casserole dish (9 x 12-inch).
Arrange cooked broccoli on top of cheese.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine. Add to crushed crackers and mix well. Spread over top of broccoli. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes to melt cheese. Good for company and potlucks.

title: keftaidakia, cocktail meatballsgreece
directions: Mix together the meat, onion, garlic, salt, pepper, oregano and mint. Remove crusts from the bread slices and moisten in wine or water. Add bread and egg to meat. Knead mixture. Shape into 1 balls, dust with flour and saute in equal amounts of olive oil and butter. When meatballs are cooked and browned on all sides, place immediately in covered casserole and keep warm until ready to serve. Makes 1 1/2-2 dozen.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with crabmeat.
Spread on bread or crackers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan on top.
Heat and brown at 350°.

title: oxtails
directions: Sprinkle oxtails with salt, pepper and paprika. Dredge in flour.
Brown on all sides in a heavy pan with fat. Remove browned oxtails and place in a roasting pan.
Mix carrots, onions, cloves, celery, tomatoes, bay leaves and water together.
Pour over browned oxtails in a roasting pan.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven until tender. Remove cover the last 1/2 hour of cooking. Stir occasionally.

title: crab dip(party-time treats)
directions: Mix together all ingredients and sprinkle with some grated cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sole curry
directions: In a wide frying pan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add shallots, curry and fish.
Turn heat to high and gently shake. Turn fish over carefully.
Cook for a total of 3 to 5 minutes until fish flakes in thickest portion.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook noodles by directions on box.
Cool.
Combine chopped raw vegetables, Italian salad dressing and 1 large bottle Salad Supreme seasoning.
Put in a covered dish in refrigerator overnight.
Toss every now and then.
Just before serving, toss ingredients again.

title: rice pan custard
directions: Beat eggs, add hot milk, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Pour in casserole, sprinkle with nutmeg if desired.
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: foiled potato
directions: Pare potato, cut in 1/4-inch slices and place on square of heavy duty foil.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with soup mix. Wrap and seal tightly.
Roast on outside.
Grill or cook in a 375° oven for about 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Yields 1 portion.

title: 12 layer caesar salad
directions: After chopping all vegetables, layer in order that they are given.
Add cheese, bacon bits, croutons and dressing when ready to serve.

title: pudding poke cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake as directed on package for 9 x 13-inch cake.
Remove from oven.
Poke holes at once down through cake to pan with round, wood spoon handle, using turning motion to make large holes.
Holes should be at 1-inch intervals.
Only after holes are made, combine pudding mix with sugar in large bowl. Slowly stir in milk.
Beat with electric mixer at low speed for no more than 1 minute.
Do not overbeat.

title: baked taco dip
directions: Cook and drain meat. Stir in seasoning, beans and tomato sauce until well blended. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.

title: kristie's round steak in the crock-pot
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low 5 1/2 to 6 hours or on high 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
If Ranch Style beans are added, wait until the last hour to do so.
Serve over rice.

title: tomato ketchup
directions: Cook
tomatoes
until
tender;
strain
through
sieve, getting out
as much pulp as possible.
Add remaining ingredients. Ladle into sterilized jars, allowing 1/2-inch headroom. Seal. Process
in boiling water (old-fashioned water bath) 10 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Press a carton of crescent rolls into a pie pan or 9 x 13 pan - sealing the holes and making a slight rim.
Cook and drain 1 lb. bulk sausage (mild).
Drain and put on top of dough.
Sprinkle on top of sausage 1/2 cup shredded cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle on top of cheddar 1 cup of shredded swiss.
Beat 4 eggs, 3/4 cup milk, 1/4 tsp. oregano.
Pour this over the cheeses.
Bake at 350 for 25 minutes.
You can prepare and put in refrigerator and bake in the morning for quick breakfast.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Fill 9 x 13-inch baking dish with sliced peaches.
Mix 1 cup sugar with cornstarch and pour over peaches, then add water, cover with foil and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
While peaches are baking, mix 1/4 cup sugar with cinnamon.

title: red cherry pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and dash of salt; let stand 20 minutes.
Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Fill with cherry mixture.
Dot with butter.
Adjust lattice crust.
Crimp edge high. Bake in hot oven (400°) for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: deer shisk-kabobs
directions: Marinate for 24 hours.
After marinating, insert slices of garlic in roast.
Rub roast with salt.
Cook in 350° oven.
Baste with marinade drippings until roast is brown and tender.
Place roast on hot platter.
Add 1 glass current jelly to drippings, also 1/2 cup sour cream and 1 tablespoon brandy.
Stir over high heat until mixture thickens.
Garnish roast with orange strips or slices and spiced pears.

title: granny's apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking powder and salt.
In large bowl, cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, vanilla and flour mixture at low speed.
Mix well.
Stir in apples and pecans. Spoon batter into greased pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
May garnish with apple slices to serve.

title: iced pineapple muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar (do not overbeat). Add beaten eggs and beat lightly. Add dry ingredients, then pineapple and flavoring, mixing only until blended. Bake in greased muffin tin at 350° for about 20 minutes. Do not allow muffins to brown. Ice with the following icing while the muffins are still hot.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Serve with varied fruits.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked french toast
directions: Slice bread into 1/2 or 3/4-inch slices.
Place slices in one layer in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Beat ingredients (except confectioners sugar) until completely blended and granulated sugar is dissolved.
Pour mixture over bread; cover and refrigerate at least one hour (can refrigerate up to 48 hours).
Bread will soak up the liquid.
When ready to serve, heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a jellyroll pan.
Use a wide spatula to transfer slices to the pan.
Allow space between each piece.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple surprise cake
directions: Mix by hand and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit punch 1
directions: Boil 1 quart of water and sugar for 1 minute.
Cool.
Add all other ingredients.
Serve in a punch bowl with ice cubes.
Garnish with orange and lemon slices, maraschino cherries and sprigs of mint.
Serves 50.

title: potato dish
directions: Mix all together. Put in oven until it bubbles.

title: barbecued ground hog
directions: Brown meat in lard in heavy skillet.
Drain off excess lard and drippings.
Pour barbecues sauce over meat.
Simmer on stove until meat is tender.
Serve with vegetables and bread.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine oleo, flour, baking powder and milk to make a paste. Mix together the broth and condensed soup in pan; bring to a boil. Add vegetables; bring to boil again.
Pour boiling soup mixture over chicken that has been cooked, boned, chopped and placed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour paste mixture slowly over top.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate dessert dip
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt the chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly. Stir in sweetened condensed milk to smooth. Add regular milk.
Stir until blended. Transfer chocolate dip to the deep end of the pedestal of the Serve-It-All set.
Place pedestal server in the deep server.

title: fat-free cheese cake
directions: Blend first four ingredients with electric mixer at medium speed.
Blend in sour cream and egg whites.
Spray a 9-inch pie plate with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs. Pour in cheese mixture and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool; add topping of your choice.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; heat to full boil.
Keep refrigerated.

title: date balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar, soft butter, peanut butter, dates and nuts together.
Form in balls and let set for 3 hours or overnight. Put chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and paraffin in double boiler and melt.
Dip balls in mixture.

title: georgia peach pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan with 2 tablespoons of butter. Sprinkle pan with 1/4 cup sugar.
Cream remaining butter. Gradually add remaining sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and mix well.

title: hawaiian chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over wings.
Cover in leak proof container and marinate for 24 hours, turning to be sure all wings have been coated for some time.
Bake on foil covered cookie sheet at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until crispy.
Do not reuse marinade.

title: thanksgiving turkeys
directions: Open all the cookies and spread icing on each side.
On one side of the cookie, press the candy corn, fat end toward the edges to form tail feathers.

On the other cookie side, press the malted milk ball into the icing to form the turkey's body, then press the red hot in front of the malted milk ball to form its "beard." Using icing as "glue," attach the "tail" half to the "body" half. Happy Thanksgiving!

title: russian poppy seed cookies(yield: 3 dozen cookies)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 325°.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Combine water, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper in large kettle. Boil for 10 - 12 minutes.

title: minced barbecue
directions: Cook lean pork (remove all fat or bones), chopped in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients above.
Cook on high heat until hot, then cook on low for about 3 hours or until thick.
Stir frequently.
Serve on hamburger bun.
This is low calorie if you use lean pork.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup, cheese and garlic salt and cook until blended together.
Place chicken in casserole dish and place broccoli on top, then soup mixture.
Put bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together cauliflower, onion, cheese and peas.
Mix Italian salad dressing mix and mayonnaise together.
Add to cauliflower mixture and toss well.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours prior to serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in 9 1/2 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and add oil, sugar, squash and vanilla.
Mix. Add all dry ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 loaf pans, (8 x 5 x 3-inch) at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pink salad
directions: Boil pineapple for 2 minutes.
Add Jell-O and boil 2 more minutes.
Cool; fold in cottage cheese and Dream Whip.
Add nuts. Chill until firm.

title: bean hot dish
directions: Mix all together in crock-pot or large pot.
Cook 2 to 3 hours.

title: marinated brussels sprouts
directions: Pierce the 2 boxes of Brussel sprouts and cook in microwave 7 minutes.
Mix bell pepper, onion and Italian dressing, pour over brussel sprouts which have been put in a casserole dish.
Marinate 24 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: oven french fries
directions: Cut potatoes in long strips about 1/2 inch square.
Mix olive oil and seasonings together in bowl.
Stir in potatoes until covered with mixture.
Spread potatoes (one layer) on baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over potatoes.
Bake in 425° oven 50 to 60 minutes until crispy.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients, then add the last 3.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Batter will be runny.
Easy and great.
Ice when cool.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together.
Cook the corn a little before baking.
Top with cheese before baking.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sonny's pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans. Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Bring to a boil and cook hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: kris's egg souffle
directions: Beat eggs, milk and seasonings until foamy.
Put croutons on bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish (shallow), then cheese, then pour egg mixture over all.
Cook 1 hour at 325°.
Lay bacon on top when done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs, then mix all ingredients together. Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 1 deep-dish pie.

title: fig preserve cake
directions: Mash figs with a potato masher.
Mix sugar and oil together. Sift all of the dry ingredients.
Mix all together.
Bake in a greased and floured pan.
For the grease, use spray Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Spray cooking sheet and icing spatula with nonstick vegetable oil cooking spray.

title: pancit noodles
directions: Cook meat until golden brown in cooking oil.
Add garlic and onion; stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Then add 3 tablespoons of soy sauce and about 2 1/2 cups of water or more.
Simmer for 2 to 5 minutes.
Then add your noodles.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: scott's favorite garlic-cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add more milk if batter seems stiff. Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet; bake at 450° until golden brown.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Serve hot.

title: meal-in-one salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite-sizes.
Cut chicken into small pieces. Layer first 7 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan in order given.
Mix mayonnaise, salad dressing and sugar.
Spread over top of ingredients to seal.
Spread cheese over dressing and refrigerate. Salad can be made ahead and kept in refrigerator.
Makes 10 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix by hand all ingredients.
Grease 3 loaf pans.
Pour batter equally in each of them.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.

title: barbecue salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add tomato sauce and other ingredients.
Blend and chill.
Recipe can be doubled if a 4-cup mold is used.

title: dump cake
directions: Into greased 13 x 9-inch pan, dump the ingredients.
Do not mix, simply dump.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: post toasties cookies
directions: In a heavy pan, bring sugar, Karo syrup and butter to a boil. Take off of heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; stir until it melts.
Add Post Toasties; stir to coat completely.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.

title: dump cake
directions: You will need one 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour pie filling into ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle all of dry cake mix (no egg, milk or oil) evenly over pie filling.
Cut thin slices of stick butter and scatter the squares over top of cake mix checkerboard-style.
Place in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cook for 10 to 15 minutes, then cut into squares.

title: chicken spectacular casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place peeled and sliced apples in greased 9 x 9-inch square or 9-inch round baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 to 3/4 cup sugar, depending on tartness of apples.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg and mix with fork until crumbly.
Pour on top of apples.
Drizzle with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Mix together in a covered pan and bake at 250° for 6 hours. Shred meat; remove fat and bones.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Reheat and serve on buns.
(This can also be cooked in slow cooker.)

title: coconut and oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix until you have a stiff batter.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cut artichokes in pieces and place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cook spinach just until tender (don't overcook). Drain well. While still hot, mix margarine and cream cheese with the spinach. Add salt to taste. Pour over the artichokes. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 24 minutes.

title: turkey and mushroom lasagna
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, prepare lasagna noodles as label directs, using 1 tablespoon salt in water; drain.
Meanwhile, mince onion.
Slice mushrooms.
In 12-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, in 2 tablespoons hot olive or salad oil, cook onion, ground turkey and 3/4 teaspoon salt until turkey is browned. With slotted spoon, remove to bowl.
In drippings in skillet and 1 tablespoon hot olive or salad oil, cook mushrooms and 1/2 teaspoon salt until mushrooms are golden; add to ground turkey mixture in bowl.
Cool slightly; stir in shredded cheese.

title: oven barley casserole
directions: Note:
I add 1/4 cup wild rice and another cup of water.

title: mound pie
directions: Alternate layers of pecans, coconut and chocolate chips.
Pour Eagle Brand milk on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease a large, glass dish.
Place sliced potatoes into dish. Season with salt and pepper.
Add 2 cans of soup and mix well. Bake at 325° to 335°, until potatoes test done.

title: chicken yellow rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread rice in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix creamed soups, water and 1/2 onion soup in a bowl and mix well, then pour mixture over rice.
Next, lay chicken breasts on top of mixture and sprinkle remaining onion soup over chicken. Cover with aluminum foil and bake approximately 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pineapple-french dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan, then heat over low heat using a beater to blend until thick and clear.
Chill, then beat again. Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix egg yolks with cream.
Add sugar, flour, salt, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir into hot milk and cook, while stirring, over medium heat until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell. Spread with meringue (2 egg whites beaten stiff with 1/8 teaspoon cream of tartar), Cool Whip or whipped cream.
You can use graham cracker crust, chocolate or regular pie shell.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain canned pineapple well.
Cream butter and sugar, add eggs, then pineapple.
Stir in bread cubes.
Bake in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: no sugar apple cake
directions: Sift in bowl the flour, soda, baking powder and Sweet 'N Low. Add oleo, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Beat well and add 2 cups chopped apples, raisins and nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: quick-fried cheese cubes
directions: Dip cheese in combined eggs and milk; coat with crumbs. Repeat dipping and coating.
Chill.
Fry in deep hot oil (375°) for 1 to 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 28 appetizers.

title: great nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage until brown.
Melt the cheeses. Saute the onion.
Mix all together and serve with nacho chips. Will keep for several days in refrigerator.
Just heat and serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well the flour, sugar, cinnamon, oil, eggs and water.
Set aside.
Mix pumpkin, baking soda and salt.
Add to the mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add walnuts or raisins.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans or 13 ounce coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: dressed eggs
directions: Boil eggs; peel and cut in half. Take out yolk. Mash yolk; add salt and pepper. Add remaining ingredients and spoon yolks into egg whites.

title: kellogg's k bars
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Measure cereal into bowl. Combine sugar and syrup in a medium saucepan and bring to a rapid bowl, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and immediately stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cereal and combine thoroughly.
Pat into pan.
Melt the butterscotch and chocolate chips. Stir to combine well.
Spread over the bars. Cut and serve. (Do not store in refrigerator; they get very hard.)

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: In bowl, mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, ground beef, bread crumbs, egg and onions.
Shape into 6 patties.
In skillet over medium heat, cook patties a few at a time until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add bananas.
Mix flour and soda.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Add nuts.
Place in 4 floured and greased pans.
Bake at 350° until tests done to touch.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
In a measuring cup, put juice and grated rind of 1 orange, 2 tablespoons melted shortening and enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup.
Cool and add egg and dry ingredients.
Do not beat too much.
Add 3/4 cup nuts and cranberries cut in half.
Pour in loaf pan.

title: steak casserole
directions: Brown steaks on both sides in hot oil or Crisco.
Place in baking dish. Slide 1 or 2 onions on top of steaks.
Place mushrooms on top of onions.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over top. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Heat asparagus liquid; add margarine.
Mix 1 cup water and flour.
Pour slowly into boiling mixture.
Stir; add cheese and melt.
Make 3 layers of asparagus, crackers and nuts.
Pour sauce over all layers.
Sprinkle crackers and nuts on top. Bake at 475° until brown, about 5 minutes.

title: pizzelles (chocolate)
directions: Mix together and if still sticky, add more flour. Refrigerate 2 hours before using.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; fold in Cool Whip.
Let set for 30 minutes or 1 hour in refrigerator before serving.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Add to Jell-O the heated cherry syrup and enough boiling water to make 1 cup.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved. Cool to room temperature.
Add the Coke.
Stir well and add drained, chopped cherries, nuts and pineapple. Chill until set.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Prepare the same as for Buttermilk Biscuits.
These will be fluffier.

title: lime pickles
directions: Mix raw cucumbers in lime and first 2 gallons of water.
Soak for 24 hours; then rinse 3 times.
Soak 3 additional hours in ice and water.
Remove carefully and drain.
Make the syrup.
Stir remaining ingredients together until dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 3 or 4 hours (or overnight).
Add pickling spice to taste.
Boil 35 minutes and fill jars with cucumbers and syrup.
Leave 1/2-inch headspace and seal jars.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour half of the batter in a Bundt pan.
Cover with 1 cup brown sugar and 1 cup nuts.
Pour remaining batter over sugar and nuts, covering completely.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool and glaze.

title: risotto
directions: Saute onion in 1/4 cup butter in large skillet until golden brown.
Add rice and stir until rice turns yellow.
Add broth and sherry.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Cover and let simmer 15 to 20 minutes, until liquid is absorbed.
Add remaining 1/4 cup butter and stir in cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Serve with favorite fruits.

title: italian beef
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut slits in roast, insert garlic cloves.
Combine all other ingredients in Dutch oven pot, add roast and cover.
Bake in oven about 2 hours, cool slightly. Slice thin, then place back in pot and cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours longer.
Serve on Italian bread.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, 1/2 can onions and vegetables.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered for 5 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken until tender, then remove chicken from bones and cut in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients except chicken and tortillas.
Reserve some cheese to put on top.
Make layers in buttered casserole with tortillas quartered on bottom, then chicken, then cheese mixture.
End with grated cheese on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: quick chicken marengo
