directions: Mix the flour with the oregano and basil in a plastic bag. Put 6 to 8 pieces of chicken in the bag at a time and shake until all chicken is coated with flour mixture.
Lightly brown the chicken pieces in margarine or butter.
Transfer to a 4-quart saucepan and add the garlic, onion, pepper, tomatoes and mushrooms.
(Vegetables could be sauteed briefly in the skillet first to bring out their flavor.)
Cover the saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over wide noodles or rice.

title: apple walnut rice stuffing
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan on medium-high heat.
Add celery, onion and poultry seasoning.
Cook and stir until onion is tender.
Add broth and bring to boil.
Stir in apples, rice and cinnamon; cover.
Remove from heat, let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in walnuts and parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter salad dressing
directions: Combine peanut butter, salt, sugar and hot water.
Boil until thick.
Pour over apples.

title: chicken saltimbocco
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle sage and pepper over chicken. Place a slice of Proscuitto on top. Roll up jelly roll style and secure with wooden toothpicks.
Place butter in a shallow dish. In another shallow dish, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Dip chicken first in melted butter, then roll in crumbs. Place chicken in shallow baking dish. Bake 40 minutes until tender. Remove toothpicks and serve.

title: peking roast
directions: Cut slits into roast.
Insert onion and garlic into slits. Put meat in a bowl and slowly pour vinegar over it.
Add enough water to cover the meat.
Cover with plastic wrap and place in refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours.
Pour vinegar off and place meat in a large heavy pot.
Brown in oil until very dark on both sides. Pour coffee and 2 cups water over the meat and cover with lid. You may need to add a little water during cooking.
Add salt 20 minutes before serving.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until done.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar until creamy. Stir in vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into pie shell. Add topping of choice (cherry, blueberry or strawberry).
Chill pie several hours before serving.

title: oriental meatballs
directions: Mix all together.
Make into small round balls and deep fry.

title: miss lois' chicken pie
directions: In a 4-quart pan (or pressure cooker) put chicken, celery, onion and just enough water to cover chicken.
Boil (or pressure cook) mixture until chicken is tender.

title: chicken spinach parmesan
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese and oregano in small bowl.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Set aside remaining.
Arrange pieces in a 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: cranberry-glazed cornish hens
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine cranberry sauce, mustard, gravy and orange peel.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until glaze is smooth.
Cut hens in half lengthwise, rinse and pat dry. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place hens on a rack with drip pan, skin side down; brush hens generously with glaze. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn hens, brush with glaze and bake for 30 minutes, or until juices run clear when pricked with a fork. While roasting, brush often with glaze.
Serve on a bed of wild rice and garnish with orange slices.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: meatza pizza
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients thoroughly and form pie crust with this mixture in a 9-inch pie pan.
Cover meat with the tomato paste.
Sprinkle with the mushrooms and sharp cheese.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Place in a 350° oven and bake 30 minutes.
Cut and serve like pie.

title: frozen fruit shake
directions: Place the banana, strawberries and mineral water in a blender. Process on medium speed until smooth.
Pour the fruit shake into two frosted glasses, decorating the rims with the fresh strawberries, if desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Wash rice and place in melted butter in an oblong baking dish. Spread over bottom of dish.
Take 1/2 can of each of the soups and mix with the 3/4 can of water.
Pour over rice.
Place chicken pieces in casserole on top of rice and soup mixture.
Mix the other 1/2 can of each of the 3 soups together (no water added) and pour over chicken.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 1 1/2-quart glass baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour, oats, cinnamon and butter in bowl.
Spoon over apples.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: west indies salad
directions: In large glass bowl, mix crabmeat and vegetables.
Mix other ingredients well and pour over crabmeat.
Cover bowl with ice cubes and refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and pull meat from bone.
Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup well and add chicken.
Pour into casserole dish.
Melt margarine and mix with crushed crackers.
Sprinkle cracker mixture over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, approximately 20 minutes.

title: kansas city steak strips
directions: Cut meat into even strips.
Heat half the butter in a skillet. Add meat.
Saute over medium-high heat until meat is brown and cooked to your liking.
Do not overcook.
Remove meat.
Keep warm.

title: marinade for swordfish
directions: Marinate at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours.

title: red rice and gravy with shrimp
directions: Make a light brown roux.
Pour water on top.
Add tomato sauce and vegetables.
Cook until thick.
Add shrimp.
Cook until shrimp are red in color and eat over rice.

title: party squash
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
The last 5 minutes, put buttered bread crumbs or crushed potato chips on top.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips with butter and let cool. Add pecans and marshmallows.
Shape into a roll.
Roll in shredded coconut. Slice.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Layer vegetables in dish.
In another bowl mix soup, sour cream, cheese, onion and salt.
Pour this over the beans and corn.
Spread crushed crackers over top of casserole.
Spread almonds on top of crackers.
Melt margarine and pour this over top of casserole. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in lemon extract and 7-Up.
Add flour.
Pour into a greased flour cake pan.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Whip the cream cheese until fluffy; beat in sugar and milk. Fold Cool Whip into mixture and spread over cooled crust.
Spread blueberry pie filling over top of this mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: kentucky corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, flour, sugar and salt.
Add corn, milk and butter. Mix and pour into large greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then stir.
Stir after 10 more minutes.
Bake 40 minutes longer (1 hour in all) until set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter popcorn balls
directions: Heat sugar and syrup to boiling while stirring constantly over medium heat. Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Mix well and add nuts.
Pour over popcorn while stirring to mix and coat. Form into balls and enjoy!

title: layered cauliflower salad
directions: In a large resealable bowl put chopped lettuce, bite size pieces of cauliflower, chopped onion, Mozzarella cheese and crumbled fried bacon.
Top this off with 1 cup mayonnaise and 1 cup sugar, blended together to make a dressing.
Seal the bowl tightly and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
Prior to serving, toss the salad.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Dump in all ingredients and stir well. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: barbecue marinade
directions: In large bowl mix first seven ingredients well.
Add steaks and allow to marinate at least 30 to 60 minutes.
Cook on grill to taste.

title: tacos
directions: Heat shells in oven (325°) until crisp.
Simmer all ingredients for 45 minutes, thickening with 1 tablespoon flour if needed.
Spoon filling into taco shells.
Top with chopped lettuce, tomatoes and shredded cheese.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: In skillet, saute onion in 1/4 cup butter until tender but not brown. Stir in drained mushrooms, flaked crab, cracker crumbs, parsley, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Spread mixture over flounder fillets. Roll fillets and place seam side down in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Make cream sauce with butter, flour and milk.
When smooth, add onion and cheese and stir until melted.
Add beaten egg yolks and spinach, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Set casserole in pan of hot water to bake.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.

title: sausage cake(moist cake)
directions: Cream sausage and sugars.
Sift dry ingredients together. Alternately add coffee and dry ingredients to sausage and sugar mixture.
Fold in nuts and dates that have been dusted with flour. Bake at 325° in tube or loaf pan, which has been greased and floured, for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
I prefer hot sausage (try extra sage).
Serves 16 to 18.

title: grandma bea's famous "sand tarts"
directions: Mix in usual way.
Beat up whole eggs and brush cookie tops. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Place 1 nut on each cookie. Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes a large amount.

title: beef with beer and herbs
directions: Fry bacon crisp; remove and reserve. Saute garlic, onions and beef in drippings. Add salt. In separate pan, make sauce of butter, flour and beer. Pour over beef, etc. Add other spices and vinegar. Simmer. Serve over rice. Three recipes feed 26 people.

title: key lime pie* * * * *
directions: Mix gelatin, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in saucepan.
Beat egg yolks, lime juice and water together; stir into gelatin mixture. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in grated peel.
Add enough coloring for a pale green color.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until thickened.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add remaining sugar gradually and beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold gelatin mixture into egg whites; fold in cream.
Spoon into chocolate crust; chill until firm.
Spread with additional whipped cream and sprinkle grated lime peel around edge.

title: easy chocolate cookies(no bake)
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in saucepan; bring to boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Quickly add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter or margarine; spread mixture onto pan.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello according to quick-set directions. When partially set, mix mandarin oranges and mixed fruit into jello. Pour into mold.

title: french cake
directions: Beat
together
sugar and egg.
Add cocoa, cinnamon and milk, very slowly.
Stir in flour.
Add baking soda dissolved in
the jelly.
Pour
into
loaf pan.
Scatter some nuts over top.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 40 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix soup mix and flour.
Stir in milk.
Add potatoes; mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream almond sauce
directions: Saute chicken in butter until golden brown, about 3 minutes per side.
Remove from skillet. Add onion and garlic.
Cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes.
Add tomato paste and flour.
Stir until blended and smooth.
Gradually add chicken stock and sherry. Cook and stir about 5 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Return chicken to skillet.
Add almonds, tarragon, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until tender.

title: elegant fruit-cheese salad
directions: Combine lettuce, cheese and celery in large salad bowl. Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, onion, mustard and salt in separate bowl.
Pour this mixture over lettuce to coat lightly.
Toss. Add orange sections, cranberry sauce and avocado.
Toss gently. Pass remaining dressing.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour, shortening and salt.
Chop fine.
Add vinegar to cup containing beaten egg.
Fill cup with water.
Add all at once to flour mixture and combine, using hands.
Can be stored in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Makes 3 (2 crust, 9-inch) pies.

title: spice ornaments
directions: Mix together well; pat out 1/2 inch thick.
Roll between 2 pieces of waxed paper.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheets and let dry for 24 to 48 hours.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Bring sour cream and butter to a boil.
Add sugar, soda and salt together and set aside to cool to lukewarm.
Add remaining ingredients and knead to elastic stage.
Place in greased bowl and let rise.

title: carrots lyonnaise
directions: Cut up carrots and cook in the bouillon cube and water until almost tender.
Melt butter.
Add onions and cook, covered, for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add carrots and stock.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Chop onion and saute in 3 teaspoons butter.
Add water and chicken cubes.
Boil about 3 minutes.
Add broccoli and cook for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and add 3 cups milk, egg bow noodles and cubed cheese.
Simmer slowly in crock-pot for about 2 to 3 hours or on stove over low heat.
Check every once in awhile so it does not burn.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix; stir well. Spread bean mixture evenly in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish. Layer remaining ingredients: guacamole, sour cream, black olives, tomatoes, onions, chilies and Monterey Jack cheese. Serve with corn chips. Makes 6 cups.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain off grease.
Add spices and tomato sauce.
Simmer sauce while cooking noodles.
Drain noodles. Layer noodles, sauce and cheese, alternately.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: country potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, with skins on, for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Peel and grate potatoes.
Heat together oleo and soup.
Add onion, grated cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Mix with potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix together corn flakes and butter.
Put on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Can be refrigerated overnight.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all together by hand. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Top with cream cheese icing.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour in uncooked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, onion, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, egg and 1/2 cup sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Pat into rectangular shape, cover with thin slices of Mozzarella cheese and roll up like a jelly roll, sealing ends.
Place in shallow baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and pour off excess fat.

title: creamy orange milkshake
directions: In blender container combine ingredients in order listed. Blend until smooth, scraping sides as necessary.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Stays thick in refrigerator.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine soup and water in large bowl to make a smooth sauce. Add celery, nuts, chicken and mushrooms one at a time; stir after each addition. Fold in one can of noodles and pour into a well-greased 4-quart greased casserole. Sprinkle the remaining can of noodles over the top. Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and drain on paper towels.
Crumble. In bacon grease, fry onion until brown.
Add ketchup, brown sugar and the crumbled bacon.
Simmer 15 minutes and add green beans. Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs and milk.
Stir until well blended.
Add pecans and stir until mixed well.
Stir while pouring into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° until done.
Test to see if done by inserting knife blade in center of pie.
If it comes out clean, pie is done.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan; press over bottom and 1-inch up the sides to form a crust.
Bake 14 to 19 minutes until golden brown.
Cool.
In a small bowl, combine sour cream and
horseradish and blend until smooth. Spread evenly over cool crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse beans.
Put in a big heavy 3-quart pot; add water, ham and sausage.
Cook uncovered.
Add chopped onion, celery, green pepper, thyme and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Stir often.
Season to taste with hot pepper, salt and black pepper.
Cook until beans are done.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: very moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix together and bake according to cake mix directions. Enjoy!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Place oysters in layers in baking dish alternately with cracker crumbs and seasonings, onion and celery.
When dish is full, add the oyster liquor and sufficient milk to moisten.
Cover with crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour. The last 10 minutes, turn oven up and bake until cracker crumbs are browned golden.
Serve hot!

title: hot rum lemonade(yields 1 serving)
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2 cup glass measure or in ceramic or glass mug.
Heat in microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until warmed.
Do not boil.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake in loaf or round pan.
Put 1/2 cup of water in bottom of pan.
Cook at 350° for one hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: cheesy lasagna
directions: Combine beef, onion and green pepper in a large skillet; cook until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat. Drain off drippings. Add next 5 ingredients; simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions, omitting salt; drain. Combine cottage cheese, sour cream and cream cheese; mix well. Layer half of each: the noodles, cottage cheese mixture, meat mixture and Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Mix soup, sour cream and lemon juice; pour over chicken bits to cover.
Sprinkle with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Cook in 350° oven until it bubbles through.
Ready to serve.

title: taco casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and add the can of tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Mix cottage cheese and sour cream together in a bowl. Crush up taco chips.
Take a 2-quart casserole dish or pan and pour a layer of hamburger mix, then chips, then the sour cream. Then sprinkle Monterey Jack cheese on top and repeat layers.
You may add beans if desired or sausage.
You may also add sliced black olives on top of sour cream mixture if desired.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over cucumbers. Add dill or parsley; mix well.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours. Serves 4.

title: holiday jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; add pineapple, bananas, strawberries and nuts. Let jell in refrigerator for about 1 hour.
Pour 1/2 mixture into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Let jell in refrigerator about 10 to 15 minutes and spread sour cream on top. Pour remaining Jell-O as top layer.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
May want to garnish for holidays.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Whip cream until thickened but not too stiff.
Fold in sugar gradually and add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted flour and mix until smooth.
Bake in square pan in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and ice with boiled frosting or Seven Minute Frosting.

title: punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
Will freeze into 3 1/2 gallons of punch.
For each 1/2 gallon add 2 quarts of 7-Up when ready to use.
Makes punch for approximately 50 people.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place raw meat on bottom of Dutch oven.
Layer the celery, carrots, onions and potatoes in that order.
Mix tomato juice, tapioca, salt and sugar together. Pour over vegetables and cover. Bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: italian tv mix
directions: Mix in large glass bowl the peanuts, noodles, Chex and pretzels.
Set aside.
(Combination of ingredients may be varied according to taste; use 8 cups.)

title: orange juice cake
directions: Follow instructions on cake mix using ingredients given here.

title: english trifle
directions: Mix the strawberries and jello (do not add water).
Place in bottom of bowl.
Pinch up angel food cake and put on top of strawberry mixture.
Mix the pudding and milk; beat until thickened (let set).
Place on top of cake in bowl.
Place bananas on top of pudding and Cool Whip on top of all.
Refrigerate.

title: tuna on a shoestring
directions: In large bowl, separate tuna into chunks.
Add carrots, celery, onion and salad dressing.
Toss until tuna is well coated with dressing.
Just before serving, add shoestring potatoes by folding into mixture.
Do not add shoestring potatoes to any mixture not being used; potatoes get soggy and ruin mix.
Eat immediately all mix with potatoes in it.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery powder, paprika, garlic, salt and pepper in large dish.
Dip each breast in sour cream mixture, coating well.
Place in baggie and refrigerate overnight.
Next day remove chicken and roll in bread crumbs.
Arrange in single layer in baking dish.
At this point, dish can be covered with foil and frozen.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix together coconut, powdered sugar and oleo.
Add Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Place in refrigerator to get stiff, about 2 hours.
Put chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler to melt.
Remove coconut dough and make into small balls. Dip into chocolate and put on wax paper to harden.

title: hot links casserole
directions: Cut up sausages, carrots and potatoes.
Place in a Pyrex dish. Mix cream of chicken soup, 1 package onion soup and 2 cups water. Pour over meat and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna al dente; drain.
Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella and Italian cheeses, 3 eggs and salt and pepper; set aside.
Brown and crumble ground beef in oil with garlic and onion.
Mix tomatoes and tomato paste (add spices and herbs as desired).
Add browned meat mixture; cook at low temperature.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off all grease.
Cool.
Chop 1 head lettuce.
Dice 2 tomatoes.
Chop green onions.
Shred cheese. Pour chips over other ingredients.
Mix Ranch dressing mix according to directions.
Add kidney beans.
Pour dressing over all ingredients; mix lightly.
Serves 15 people.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan, stir together the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix in the milk, oil and vanilla. Mix with fork until smooth.
Stir in the nuts and spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with the brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour in 1 3/4 cup hottest tap water over batter.
Bake 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: simple chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken breasts into casserole dish.
In mixing bowl mix soups and rice.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cook covered for 1 hour.
Cook and brown uncovered for 30 minutes.
Then remove; let stand about 15 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: In small iron skillet, slowly brown rice, onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Add spices, then add hot water with chicken bouillon dissolved in it.
Cover.
Cook on lowest heat for 15 minutes.
This is very good with enchiladas and refried beans.

title: gourmet crab ring
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water to soften; stir over hot water until dissolved.
Beat into cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in next 5 ingredients and 2 tablespoons parsley.
Pour into a 3-cup ring mold.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or until set.
To serve, turn out on plate.
Garnish with remaining parsley.
Place parsley sprigs in center.
Serve on Escort crackers.
Makes 3 cups spread.

title: rosti
directions: Shred the potatoes. Cook potatoes, onion and garlic in small amount of oil to brown slightly. Fry bacon until crisp. Put potato mixture in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Crumble bacon over the top and slightly mix. Shred cheese over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese melts.
Serves 4. Recipe from Southern Baptist representative Nina Pinkston in Germany. From Foreign Mission Study 1994.

title: southern corn fritters
directions: Drain corn well, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, parsley flakes and paprika.
Combine eggs, melted butter or margarine and liquid drained from corn. Mix well.
Add to dry ingredients all at once and stir until smooth.
Fold in drained corn.
Drop batter from a tablespoon into deep fat, heated to 375° and fry a few at a time, until golden brown on all sides.
Remove from fat; drain on absorbent paper. Keep hot while frying remaining fritters.
Roll in confectioners sugar just before serving.
Makes 20 fritters.

title: two bean chowder
directions: Soak beans in water overnight or for quick soak, bring beans and water to a boil for 2 minutes.
Cover and let stand 1 hour. Add ham hock to beans.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove ham hock and cut up meat.
Mash a portion of the beans.
Return meat to soup.
Add onion, garlic, celery, carrot and crushed red pepper. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add milk and heat.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serves 6 to 8. May be made ahead and frozen.

title: butterscotch treats
directions: Melt peanut butter and morsels on low heat.
Add corn flakes and mix well.
Spoon on waxed paper.

title: impossible pie
directions: In blender, mix and then place in an ungreased 10-inch pie pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped cabbage with cheese
directions: Cut cabbage in desired shape.
Place in kettle with generous amount of water.
Add salt to water just before cooking is completed.
Drain.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients for crust.
Press into an 8-inch square dish and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: butternut squash pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Mix thoroughly, then add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake 10 minutes at 400° then for 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 medium size pies.

title: ham-it-up crescent snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into four long rectangles. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Place one slice ham on each rectangle.
Spread ham slices with mustard; sprinkle with cheese. Starting with the shortest side, roll up each rectangle and press edges to seal.
Coat rolls with sesame seed.
Cut each of the four rolls into five slices, forming 20 slices in all.
Place each slice, cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
To make ahead, prepare, cover and refrigerate up to 2 hours before baking.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna in boiling, salted water for about 15 minutes.

title: blender chocolate fudge
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in blender and mix well.
Pour in pie shells.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven while center will shake lightly.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels with peanut butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring until blended.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Press half of mixture into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill.
Set remainder aside.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix powdered sugar slowly with 2 eggs and cream cheese. Spread over cake mixture and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: onion pie
directions: Saute onion in oleo and set aside.
Mix Jiffy mix, egg, milk and cream-style corn.
Pour batter into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. To onion add sour cream and cheese.
Spoon over batter.
Top with extra cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fronie's homemade cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve 1 teaspoon of sugar in water (110° to 115°), then add yeast and let dissolve and foam.
Scald the milk, remove from heat and add shortening, sugar and salt.
When milk mixture cools to lukewarm, add the yeast mixture and beaten eggs.
Add 2 cups flour and beat with mixer, add remaining flour slowly until dough is stiff, elastic and non-sticky.
Turn out on floured cloth and knead 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and flip over until all is covered.
Place in unheated oven and cover with cloth.
Boil a pan of water and place in the bottom of the oven.
Keep oven door closed until dough doubles in size.
Punch the dough in the middle to release air, then turn out on floured surface and roll into large rectangle.
Brush with melted butter (approximately 3/4 stick).
Sprinkle with 2 cups brown sugar and dust entire surface with cinnamon.
Sprinkle with finely chopped pecans, if desired. Roll up like a jelly roll and slice 1-inch thick.
Place in greased pan, cut side down.
Be sure they are 1 inch apart.
Allow dough to rise, uncovered, the same as before until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook & chop chicken. Mix chicken, soup, sour cream & poppy seed and spread in greased 9 X 13 dish. Mix & spread on top of chicken Bake at 350° for 30-40 min. until bubbling. Serve with rice (any kind).

title: marinated beef tenderloin
directions: Mix Worcestershire, mustard, Italian dressing mixes, water and ketchup; pour over tenderloin and marinate about 8 hours.
Bake on roasting pan in 425° oven for approximately 35 minutes, basting occasionally or until thermometer reaches 150°.
Wrap in aluminum foil, shinny side in, until ready to slice and serve.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar together.
If too stiff, add a little milk.
Set aside.
Spread 1/2 of the Cool Whip in the bottom of a rectangular glass casserole.
Slice cake thin.
Layer with the Cool Whip, cheese, sugar mixture, more cake, then more Cool Whip.
Top with cherries.
Chill.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Put 1 tablespoon of mixture in the center of won ton skins, then pull together and deep fry until golden brown.
Keep oil about 350° to 400°.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together in a large bowl.
Put butter, Crisco, cocoa and water in a saucepan; bring to a rapid boil. Pour over flour mixture; stir well.
Beat eggs and buttermilk; stir in soda and cinnamon.
Add to chocolate mixture; mix well. Pour into greased and floured 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: warm chicken roll-ups
directions: Mix chicken, nuts and mayonnaise with a fork.
Sprinkle a tiny bit of fresh lemon in.
Unfold crescent rolls.
Shape into 4 rectangles, pinching seams to make a smooth surface.
Spread chicken mixture onto each of four rectangles, not all the way to the edges.
Cut each roll into bite size pieces.
Place on cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake approximately 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add pumpkin, pie spice, vanilla and milk.
Pour in pan.

title: overnight buns
directions: Mix yeast, 1/2 cup warm water and 2 teaspoon sugar in small bowl and let raise until foamy to the top.
In large bowl, mix 4 cups warm water, sugar and oil.
Add yeast mixture, then flour and salt.
Mix all ingredients together and knead real good.
Grease hands with Crisco when working out and put flour in the bottom of pan when working down.
Make up at 6:00 p.m.
Work down at 8:00 p.m.
Shape into buns at 10:00 p.m.
Bake the next morning.
Dough shouldn't be sticky.
The less flour you use the better.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Can be made in the day, also.

title: taco sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Mix in a large pan with other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 1 1/2 hours on low heat.
Makes 9 pints.

title: peanut butter krunchies
directions: Bring the sugar and syrup to a boil.
Whip in the peanut butter.
Fold in the Special K cereal and cornflakes.
Spoon onto wax paper and let dry.

title: molded shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup to boil.
Stir in cream cheese; add gelatin and cool.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put in mold (greased) and refrigerate.

title: mini blinies
directions: Cut crusts off bread.
Roll flat with rolling pin.
Spread with cream cheese mixture (cream cheese, lemon juice and 1/2 cup sugar).
Roll.
Dip in melted butter, then cinnamon/sugar mixture (1 c. sugar and cinnamon).

title: chili cornbread
directions: Mix corn muffin mix as directed on box.
Pour half in loaf. Spread on chili, cheese and onion.
Pour rest of batter in pan and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.

title: cranberry fruit bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in bowl. Add shortening and cut in. Combine juice, egg and zest and beat lightly. Add to dry ingredients. Do not overmix.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.

Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour until golden brown and wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on rack 10 minutes, then turn out bread and cool completely.

title: tandoori chicken
directions: Combine yogurt with minced onion, minced piece of ginger, all seasonings listed and lemon juice.
Cut gashes into chicken legs and thighs.
Pour yogurt marinade over them and let marinate in the fridge overnight.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place one can of rolls, unrolled to cover bottom of dish. Cream together the cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla. Spread over roll dough. Top with second can
of rolls, unrolled as first one.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes until brown. Cool and ice with confectioners sugar, mixed with enough water to make glaze.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and drop by tablespoon into deep fat.

title: pistachio custard puffs
directions: Heat to rolling boil the water and butter.
After butter is melted add flour, all at once.
Stir rapidly until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat 1 egg at a time into mixture with a mixer until smooth.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until dry, puffed and golden brown.
Cool.

title: orange fluff stuff
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese and dry jello together. Add oranges. Stir gently. Chill. Serve chilled.

title: shrimp bake
directions: Arrange shrimp in baking dish. Mix last 4 ingredients and pour over shrimp. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Make the cake mix according to package and bake in a 12 x 18-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.

title: pea salad
directions: Line bottom of salad bowl with shredded lettuce or spinach leaves.
Layer remaining ingredients in order in which they are listed.
Place in refrigerator and let set about 12 hours or overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients until workable, but not dry. Brown in skillet and cook in spaghetti sauce until done through; approximately 1 hour.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate and let stand overnight.

title: rich dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large bowl;
sprinkle yeast in and stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, eggs and 2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough. Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Put in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Shape into egg-size pieces; arrange pieces on greased baking sheet.
Allow to rise about 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Brush tops with melted butter if desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put all ingredients but chips in mixing bowl and mix well. Put in a baking dish. Crush chips in the bag and sprinkle on top. Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: sausage bread
directions: Remove casing from sausage.
Cook sausage in skillet, stirring occasionally, until well done.
Remove from heat and add beaten eggs.
Roll dough into 18 x 10-inch rectangle.
Cover dough with sausage, pepperoni, Mozzarella and grated cheese.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush top with egg. Bake in 400° oven for 35 minutes.

title: date-nut loaf
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Cut in shortening until like coarse meal.
Make a well and add milk and egg.
Mix until dampened.
Add nuts and dates.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking (in 9 x 5-inch pan).
When cool, cut in small chunks.
Put in a bowl and mix with Cool Whip, lightly.

title: turkey patties
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, blending well with hands.
Shape mixture into hamburger-size patties.
Arrange patties on a nonstick baking sheet and broil 3 to 4-inches from heat for 5 to 7 minutes or until lightly browned.
Turn and continue to broil an additional 3 to 5 minutes or until done. Serves 6.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and chopped nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased 8- inch pans at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until done.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pineapple punch
directions: In punch bowl dissolve sugar in lemon juice.
Blend in Hawaiian pineapple juice, cranberry juice cocktail and soda.
Add sherbet, stirring until softened.
Garnish with pineapple chunks or rings and maraschino cherries. Makes 48 (4 ounce) servings.

title: carnation famous fudge(makes 2 pounds)
directions: Butter 8-inch square pan.
In medium saucepan, combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, morsels, vanilla and nuts.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until marshmallows melt completely.
Pour into pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; beat according to cake package directions.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake for 50 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minute; turn out.
Cool completely and frost as desired.

title: creamy apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the first 2 ingredients; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup for topping.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon to reserved topping.
Mix and set aside.
Press remaining mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange apples over base. Blend sour cream and eggs; spread evenly over apples.
Sprinkle reserved topping over apples.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown and bubbly.
Serve warm and refrigerate leftovers.

title: rice soup with boiled eggs
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Add rice and eggs; mix. Serve hot.

title: eye of round with rosemary
directions: Season meat 2 days before cooking (or less).
Rub entire surface of meat liberally with mix of seasonings.
Wrap tightly in foil; refrigerate.
One hour before cooking, bring meat to room temperature.
Brown on all sides in 1 teaspoon shortening.
Place in shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 300° until done or 15 minutes per pound for rare, 20 minutes per pound for medium and 22 minutes per pound for well done.
Best served at room temperature.

title: crock-pot italian beef
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low all day.
Cool and slice.
Serve on rolls or buns with a bowl of "au jus" for dipping.

title: caramel rice krispie treats
directions: First, melt caramel and water over low heat in a medium pot. Second, after melting caramels, remove from stove and add the Rice Krispies and stir.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Press mixture in the pan.
Chill 30 minutes.
Cut into medium bars.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Combine in mixing bowl.
Mix and place in shallow casserole dish and top generously with crushed potato chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: knock 'em over chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Heat oven to 350°. Layer coconut and pecans in bottom of pan. Mix cake mix according to instructions on the box. Pour batter over coconut and pecans. Melt cream cheese and butter together in microwave.
Mix powdered sugar into cream cheese mixture; stir until smooth. Pour mixture over entire cake mix batter. Bake 40 to 50 minutes. Serve out of pan with Cool Whip on top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs, pumpkin, Crisco and water; beat well with mixer. Set aside.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Add nuts and mix well with the moist ingredients by hand.
Do not use mixer.
Grease and fill 3 loaf pans half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test after 35 minutes.
May not take a full hour.

title: chili sauce relish
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 3 or 4 hours.
"Can" like tomatoes. (Place in sterile canning jars, seal and process in a boiling water bath for 10 minutes.)
Great with scrambled eggs, chicken or fish.

title: cardinal french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shake until well mixed before each time used.
Makes 1 pint.

title: meat cheese ball
directions: Chop beef very fine and slice green onions.
Use tops as well. Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and into a ball.
Chill well. Can be rolled in chopped nuts, if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Saute diced chicken until tender.
Mix soups and milk.
Add chicken and rice. Mix well.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan or 3-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 275° until heated through and cheese is melted.
I heat the soup and milk mixture before adding chicken and rice.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine milk, water, egg yolks and flour.
Cook until comes to a boil and thickens.
Add coconut and vanilla. Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar slowly while beating.
When mixture is stiff, top pie and bake in 375° oven until meringue browns lightly.

title: tuna vegetable slaw
directions: Break tuna into large chunks in a bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and lemon juice in a bowl.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients to tuna; mix well.
Pour dressing over salad; toss lightly.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mother's pecan pie
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until thickened.
In another bowl, beat eggs until they are fluffy.
Add slowly to hot hot mixture. Add vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 375° until pie shell is well done, 25 to 30 minutes, depending on oven.
Use uncooked pie shell.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend cookies in a blender.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
Mix pudding and milk; fold in Cool Whip. Mix with creamed mixture.

title: cheese topping
directions: Grate cheese; mix mayonnaise, dressing and cheese together. Spread on thick or thin slices of bread.
Put oven on broil; bake until cheese is melted 3 to 4 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and form into a ball; pinch off small bite size balls.
Place in muffin tins or cookie sheet; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook until lemon is tender.
Cook and skin beets and cut into pieces.
Put in syrup and heat until boiling.
Put into hot jars. Makes beets very shiny.

title: the "original girl scout cookie"
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill for about an hour.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut out and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Good for Christmas cookies.

title: mama's cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add milk to make stiff dough.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: veal casserole
directions: Brown veal in margarine.
Take out and put in casserole.
Brown onion, garlic, allspice, mushrooms, tomato paste and flour together.
Simmer stock and wine separately for 5 minutes.
Add to mixture and pour over veal.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 50 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Put shredded cabbage in large bowl; sprinkle with sugar.
Toss until mixed and cover.
Chill 30 minutes.
Mix lemon juice and mayonnaise in small bowl.
Pour over cabbage.
Add carrot and green pepper.
Toss to mix well.
Serves 8.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and butter together.
Add other ingredients. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 2 pies or 16 tarts.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put into pan for serving.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients, then eggs, one at a time.
Add carrots.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 55 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in oleomargarine.
Add sour cream.
Mix lightly.
Lay out and cut into biscuits.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 minutes at 450°.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop on greased cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Bake at 350° in oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange chess pie
directions: Mix
filling
and
pour
into unbaked pie shells.
Bake until filling is set and crust is lightly browned at 350°.
To keep
the outer edges of pie shell from browning too much too soon,	cut strips of foil 2 inches wide and long enough to go around
the shell edge and crease it over to stay until pie is done.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix in bottom of pan.

title: corn meal cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a round 10 x 2-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Mix together and put in muffin tin. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. (Time may vary due to oven.) *Add bacon bits for a different taste.

title: peanut bars
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, crackers, powdered sugar.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips, spread on top.

title: mint brownie bites
directions: Melt the chocolate and butter in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring, until smooth (or melt in the microwave).
Remove from heat and cool completely.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine sugars and eggs.
Beat until thick and creamy. Stir in the extracts and chocolate mixture.
Add the flour and salt, stirring until well blended.
Stir in walnuts and chopped candy.
Spoon into buttered mini-muffin pans.
Fill 2/3 full. Bake for 15 or 20 minutes or until they begin to pull away from the sides.
Cool completely before removing from the pans.
Makes about four dozen.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in the 2 pie crusts.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.

title: new england gingersnaps
directions: Beat butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add egg and molasses.
Beat well. Sift together the flour, soda and spices.
Add to butter mixture, beating until smooth. Chill dough 2 hours.
Shape dough into 3/4-inch balls and roll in additional sugar to coat well. Place 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes.
(Cookies will puff up, then flatten.)
Cool slightly on cookie sheets. Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: baby calzone
directions: Combine Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses in small bowl and mix.
Half each biscuit horizontally making 20 thin biscuits. If kitchen is hot, refrigerate half the dough.
Shape one piece of dough into an oval about 2 1/2 x 4-inches.
Place a slice of pepperoni slightly off center on the dough.
Top with one level tablespoon of cheese mixture.
Moisten edge and fold dough over to enclose filling.
Pinch edges to seal.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: continental stroganoff
directions: Brown steak in butter. Add mushrooms. Stir in soup mix and flour. Add milk and water. Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened. Cover and cook on low heat for 45 minutes. Stir twice while cooking.
Blend in sour cream.
Heat through. Do not boil.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: artichoke & spinach dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients and spoon in hot dip bowl.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: micro fudge
directions: Mix ingredients, except nuts, and microwave for 1 minute; stir; microwave 1 more minute.
Add nuts.
Beat by hand until gloss starts to disappear.
Turn into a plate.

title: seven layer bars
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, melt butter.
Add in layer but do not stir: graham crackers, butterscotch bits, chocolate bits, coconut and walnuts.
Then pour can of sweetened condensed milk over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix yeast, sugar, eggs and warm water; beat with mixer until foamy.
Add shortening, salt and flour.
Knead together and let rise until double.
Roll out and spread with butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll into jelly roll; slice and place in a large baking dish.
Let rise again.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: mushroom puffs
directions: Saute mushrooms in olive oil and garlic.
Season with coarse black pepper and dash of Tony Chachere seasoning.
Set aside. Cream the softened cream cheese together with green onions and sauteed mushrooms.
Add seasoned salt, as needed.
Roll crescent rolls out in jelly roll fashion; fill with cream cheese mixture. Brush with egg and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° until golden brown (10 to 20 minutes); slice into one-inch pieces and serve.

title: easy chipped beef in gravy
directions: Saute slivered sandwich meat.
Prepare gravy according to directions.
Pour over meat.
Spread over baked, halved biscuits.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, onions and mustard until blended.
In oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spread sauerkraut, top with uncooked noodles.
Spoon soup mixture evenly over noodles.
Sprinkle with corned beef, then cheese.

title: banana brunch punch
directions: In a blender or food processor, blend bananas, orange juice and lemonade until smooth.
Remove half of the mixture and set aside.
Add 1 1/2 cups of warm water and 1 cup of sugar to mixture in blender; blend until smooth.
Place in a large freezer container.
Repeat with remaining banana mixture, water and sugar; add to container.
Cover and freeze until solid.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix pecans with brown sugar, egg white, powdered ginger and rind just until mixture is bound together.
Press into the bottom and a little bit up the sides of a 10 inch spring form pan.

title: peek-a-berry boos
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift first 4 ingredients.
Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs, water and extract; beat well. Blend in dry ingredients and rolled oats.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Place 1/2 teaspoon jam on each cookie.
Press jam lightly into dough.
Top with level teaspoon of dough.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: super easy main dish casserole(kids love this!)
directions: Brown ground
beef;
drain
and put in bottom of square casserole dish.
Drain
green
beans;
spread on top of ground beef.
Spread
chicken
soup
(leave
it
condensed) on top of green beans.
Salt	and pepper to taste on top of soup.
Cover with a single
layer of Tater Tots.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes until Tater Tots are done.

title: galaxy mousse
directions: In small bowl, beat egg yolks with milk.
In medium saucepan, combine gelatin with 1/2 cup sugar.
Blend in milk mixture. Let stand 1 minute.
Cook over low heat, stirring to dissolve gelatin (about 5 minutes).
Whisk in cocoa and malted milk powder. Transfer to medium bowl and refrigerate about 35 minutes until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon.
In mixer bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold into gelatin mixture, then fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage in greased 2-quart dish.
Brown beef and onion; drain and place on top of cabbage.
Place rice on top of meat and cabbage.
Pour soup and water to cover all.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage and cabbage
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, combine sausage, water and bouillon granules.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.

title: party fruit punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Add lemonade and pineapple juice.
Mix.
Pour into 1 gallon container and freeze. Remove from freezer at least 2 hours before serving.
Put in punch bowl and add Sprite at serving time.
Makes 25 cups.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese (softened).
Mix well until well blended. Add remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Mix well and chill. Shape into ball and roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: summer squash and peppers
directions: Simmer squash and peppers in a cup of water, covered.
Remove from heat and drain while there is still some body to the squash. Meanwhile, fry bacon and cook the onion in bacon fat until transparent.
Drain some of the bacon fat, leaving some of the onions for flavoring.
Crumble bacon and add bacon and onion to squash mixture; then stir in the croutons.
Pour into a casserole dish and heat in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: abe's dish
directions: In a work or large skillet, put 2 to 3 tablespoons vegetable oil and add onions and brown slightly.
Then add chicken and stir around 4 or 5 minutes.
Then add all liquids and stir, then add in vegetables and continue to stir.
When vegetables get tender, dish is ready.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chile dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Keep frozen until ready to use.
Then thaw and serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 5 large and 5 small freezer cartons.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients until crumbly.
Add water; mix well.
Add more water if needed.
Makes 3 pie crusts or 10 fried pie crusts.

title: old fashion rolls
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, sugar, Crisco and salt until warm (115° to 120°).
Stir until Crisco melts; add dry mixture.
Add eggs.
Beat with mixer at low speed for 1/2 minute.
By hand stir in enough remaining flour to make moderately stiff dough.
Shape in ball.
Place in a greased bowl.
Let rise in a warm place until double, about 1 1/4 hours.
Punch down and shape into ball.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Brush with melted Crisco. Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cinnamon-raisin biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl; cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add raisins; toss well.
Add 3/4 cup milk; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: granny's apple pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with one crust.
Place apples in crust and cover with mixture of dry ingredients.
Top with top crust.
Mix a small amount of cinnamon and sugar to sprinkle on top crust.
Dot with butter squares.
Seal and vent crust.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: fake tandoori chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chicken, to form paste. Paint chicken parts with paste.
Place in glass container, cover and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Line pan with foil and bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
To keep chicken crisp, you may need to drain about midway through cooking time.
Great served hot or cold.

title: coconut cherry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and stir into creamed mixture.
Add nuts, cherries, coconut and chocolate. Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut in 40 bars.

title: delicate lemon squares
directions: Combine dry cake mix with lemon pie filling.
Pour into ungreased jellyroll or sheet cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool and frost.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown meat.
Pat biscuits in bottom and sides of greased muffin pan.
Add other ingredients as desired.
Top with pizza or spaghetti sauce (approximately 2 tablespoons).
Then sprinkle with cheese and bake at 375° until biscuits are browned.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Let strawberries thaw out.
Drain out juice.
Put Jell-O in cup.
Fill with water to make 1 cup.
Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, half of strawberries and your cup of Jell-O.
Mix all together and bake in layers or Bundt pan for 45 to 50 minutes.
Bake at 350°.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In medium saucepan over low heat, heat butter and chocolate squares until melted.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Stir in sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating until blended.
Stir in flour, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Top with chocolate pieces.
Bake 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 30 minutes.

title: glazed lemon nut bread
directions: Cream together butter and 3/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and lemon peel; beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Stir in walnuts. Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes.
Combine lemon juice and 2 tablespoons sugar; spoon over top.
Remove from pan; cool.
Wrap; store overnight.

title: squash dressing(club member: lee ann mcraney)
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter. Mash squash and combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and bell pepper until nearly done; drain.
Place ground beef mixture and rest of ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Heat peaches with 1/3 cup sugar.
Melt butter; pour on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make batter of sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter (do not stir).
Place sliced peaches (juice and all) on top.
(No stirring again.)

title: honey whole-wheat bread(2 loaves)
directions: In large bowl, combine water, honey and yeast.
Allow to soften 5 minutes.
Add oil and whole wheat flour.
Beat 100 strokes.
Add and stir well 2 to 3 cups white flour to make stiff dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes, place in oiled bowl, cover with cloth and let rise one hour.
Punch down and knead to original size.
Cut in two pieces.
Roughly shape into loaves and place in two large (9 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Let rise (40 to 45 minutes) to top of pans (or a little above).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: In a large container with a lid, stir together broccoli florets, red onion, kidney beans, sliced olives, mushrooms, grated sharp cheddar, tomatoes, and salted sunflower seeds to taste. Separately, stir together remaining ingredients and pour over broccoli mixture.
Marinate overnight and it's ready to serve.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together thoroughly shortening, eggs and sugar.
Sift together and stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Chill dough.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Roll these in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly brown but still soft.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.
The cookies puff up at first but flatten out with crinkly tops.
Makes 2 dozen (2-inch) cookies.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon.
Cover bottom of flat, greased dish with slices of dried beef.
Arrange chicken breasts on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and spread over chicken. Best if refrigerated at this point overnight to marinate.
When ready to use, bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli; peel stems and dice into small pieces. Separate flowerets; add onions, bacon, and raisins. Combine last four ingredients and whip with a wire whisk until smooth and creamy. Amounts of sugar and vinegar may be adjusted to taste. Pour dressing over broccoli and let set 2 or 3 hours before serving.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with crumbled wafers. Roll into small balls and refrigerate.
Nuts and coconut may be added or roll the balls in them.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crumble cookies and mix with 1 stick melted butter.
Spread mixture on 11 x 13-inch pan to make crust.
Slice ice cream and put on top of crust.
Freeze.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Heat milk to scalding (bubbles form around edge of pan).
Pour milk over bread cubes.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry bars
directions: Mix all, but pie filling, together.
Pour 3/4 batter into large, greased pan.
Spread pie filling over batter.
Drop rest of batter on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Put icing on top.

title: favorite broccoli casserole
directions: Drain broccoli.
Beat together milk and eggs.
Combine all ingredients except crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Ten minutes before done, cover with crushed bacon flavored crackers.
Dot with butter.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: cheesy onion casserole
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Saute onions until clear and slightly brown.
Layer onions, 2/3 of cheese and the pepper in a 2-quart casserole.
In a saucepan, heat soup, milk and soy sauce. Pour soup mixture into casserole and stir gently.
Top with bread slices.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Push bread down under sauce; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes
more. Good served as beef or pork side dish.
Serves 8.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and cover bottom of pizza pan.
Cook as directed.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar until smooth.
This is your sauce; spread it on the cookie dough after it has cooked and cooled.
Wash fruits.
Peel kiwi and peaches; slice.
Arrange in any order you'd like.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chewie cookies
directions: Mix and place in large greased cookie sheet.
Pat flat and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cut into convenient squares while still warm.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's syrup pie
directions: Stir together beaten eggs, dark molasses syrup, sugar, melted butter and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Let cool completely.

title: mexican tea cakes(cookies)
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Cream butter; add sugar and blend thoroughly.
Mix well.
Add flour.
Form into small balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove from oven and cool slightly, about 3 minutes.
Roll immediately in powdered sugar. Repeat when cold.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time. Beat after each.

Add vanilla and chocolate; mix until blended. Sift flour, soda and salt and then add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating after each addition until batter is smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Add all ingredients in large bowl.
Add enough water to desired consistency.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours; the colder the better.

title: ground beef goulash
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in large skillet; add noodles. Combine water, broth, tomato juice and seasonings.
Pour over noodles and meat mixture.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add green pepper; cover and cook until noodles are tender.
Add mushrooms and sour cream; heat but do not boil. Makes 6 servings.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until transparent.
Add soup, turkey, mayonnaise and rice.
Put in casserole dish (1 1/2 to 2-quart) and sprinkle with corn flakes or potato chip crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mushrooms may also be added before baking.

title: oatmeal raisin cookie pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Beat together eggs, corn syrup, sugar and butter. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into crust. Place on baking sheet and bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until top is golden brown and filling is just set in center. Cool. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with shredded cheese and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: tangy vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until jello sets. Very refreshing.

title: honey dipped chicken
directions: Melt butter in shallow pan.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Roll chicken slices in mixture to coat all sides.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: string bean creole
directions: Drain beans; save 1/4 cup of liquid.
Cut bacon into small pieces; fry until almost crisp.
Add beans and reserved liquid to bacon; cook for 10 minutes.
Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes; cook until sauce is thick.
Season. Combine mixtures and pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted and crumbs are brown.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Spread bottom of baking dish with one can soup.
Steam broccoli.
Pound chicken breasts between wax paper until thin with wooden flat side of pounder.
Place moist chicken into bread crumbs.
Fry coated chicken until white and cooked through.
Place cooked chicken on top of sour already in pan and put broccoli on top.
Spread the other can of soup over broccoli and sprinkle with onion rings on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes with aluminum foil on top of pan or until bubbly.

title: flank steak
directions: Sprinkle medium flank steak with meat tenderizer.
Roll steak and place toothpicks in to hold.
Place in mixture; allow to marinate for 3 hours.
Broil steak for 25 minutes on each side and to serve as gravy over steak.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Season with garlic powder and brown in oil.
Mix onion soup mix with water.
Add soup mix and mushrooms to meat.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Thicken.
Add catsup and sour cream. Stir until mixed.

title: lo-cal milk shake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender, cover and process for 2 minutes.
Contains 50 calories.

title: friendly fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit, except strawberries and mix together in a large bowl. Sprinkle dry instant pudding mix over fruit and stir. Chill before serving.

title: mini cherry cheesecakes
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites and set aside.
Mix egg yolks and sugar, then cream in cheese.
Add egg whites.
Use mini muffin cup pans.
Butter each pan including the top edge.
Pour in graham cracker crumbs; shake and pour out.
Fill each muffin cup half full of mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Put cherry on top. Makes about 100.

title: spaghetti pizza pie
directions: Toss cooked spaghetti, Parmesan cheese and egg. Place in 9-inch pie plate. Press along bottom and sides to form crust. Mix cooked meat and spaghetti sauce. Spread meat mixture over spaghetti crust. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting into wedges. Makes 8 servings.

title: potato chocolate cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add the egg yolks, potatoes, water and vanilla; mix well.
Combine the flour, cocoa and baking powder; add to the creamed mixture.
In a small mixing bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into batter along with nuts.

title: glennie's cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then next 2 ingredients.
Sift next 4 ingredients and then mix together
with previous ingredients. Shape into a roll and refrigerate.
Cut 1/4-inch thick.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: pistachio nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate syrup, and beat 2 minutes.
Mix 1/3 of batter with the chocolate syrup.
Alternate layers of mixtures in a Bundt pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the beef and drain grease.
Put in taco seasoning and mix well.
Put beef, lettuce, cheese and corn chips in one bowl and mix well.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine eggs, margarine, sugar and flavor.
Add flour gradually.
Batter will be stiff.
Start in cold oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Slice eggs; drain and rinse shrimp.
Mix all ingredients and chill until ready to serve.

title: date crackers
directions: Put cracker on cookie sheet; add date mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Frost while warm with powdered sugar, vanilla and cream cheese mixture (thin with milk if needed).

title: burritos
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Add 1 cup water and taco mix. Simmer until thick enough.
Put in shells.
Add cheese and hot or mild pepper rings.
(Use beans if desired.)
Freeze if desired and microwave.

title: tacos
directions: Cook onion in 1 Tbsp. water in heavy skillet. Add meat & brown. Add other ingredients & cook at least 30 minutes.

title: coffee chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, soda and baking powder.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites.
Fold into batter last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer until done.

title: savory bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cut bread lengthwise in half.
Brush cut surfaces with salad dressing.
Sprinkle with oregano, cheese and paprika.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet 10 minutes.
Cut into slices.
Serves 6.

title: teriyaki kabobs
directions: Place chicken chunks and marinade in Ziploc bag and squeeze out air.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Alternate on skewers with any or all of the following:
small onions or onion chunks, whole fresh mushrooms, green pepper chunks, small canned potatoes, pineapple chunks or tomato wedges.
Cook on a barbecue grill or broil 3 to 4 inches from heat, turning after 5 to 6 minutes. Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of tea.

title: grape juice with egg(usa)
directions: Pour orange juice and grape juice in a tall glass, add sugar and salt to egg white.
Add this to the fruit juice and stir just enough to mix well.
Yields 1 serving.

title: microwave chili cheese dip
directions: Mix chili, onion rings and Cheez Whiz in a large bowl.
Cook in microwave 10 minutes (covered). Stir halfway through.

title: zucchini pie(one 9-inch)
directions: Add ingredients to zucchini.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour or until center is done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill for several hours.
Add 1/2 cup mayonnaise and serve with chips or crackers.

title: marinated three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and combine.
Add chopped green pepper.
Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Toss with beans. Chill overnight.
Before serving, toss to coat and drain.

title: zucchini loaf
directions: Mix well eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Add flour; mix.
Add soda, salt, cinnamon, baking powder, raisins and nuts. Pour into loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Can also use yellow squash.

title: skillet mac-n-beef
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat the eggs into the butter and sugar mixture with mixer.
Mix in the flour, buttermilk, soda and salt.
Add the nuts, chopped dates, coconut and candy pieces. Batter should be very stiff.
Bake at 250° in a tube pan lined with waxed paper for three hours.
When cake is done, leave in pan. Pour a mixture of 1 cup orange juice blended with 2 cups confectioners sugar over the cake.
Leave the cake in pan overnight.
The next morning, turn the cake out on a serving plate. This is a good cake to freeze.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together.
Toss all together and refrigerate before serving.

title: fruit charlotte
directions: This is a dessert much used in Palestine and is so delicious, easy and economical that it will be one of your favorites.
The fruit may be stewed fresh fruit, drained canned fruit or stewed dried fruit.
I prefer the dried, for flavor.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Place soup bone, water, salt, pepper, carrots, celery, potatoes, onions and bay leaf into slow cooking pot.
Cover and cook at setting 3 for 6 to 7 hours.
Remove soup bone and cool slightly.
Remove meat from bones and return to soup with tomatoes. Cover and slow cook an additional hour.
Noodles may be added. Makes 6 servings.

title: springtime potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes, but don't peel.
Cut up any large potatoes. Cook in boiling salted water for 15 to 20 minutes, or until tender.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve cranberry sauce in top of double boiler with Jell-O. Add rest of ingredients; pour into mold and chill overnight.

title: rolls
directions: Mix
milk,
shortening and sugar.
Place on stove.
Let it get
warm enough to melt shortening, but do not boil.
Set aside to cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in small amount of mixture. Pour
back into mixture.
Add enough flour to make a thick	paste. Cover
and
set
aside
to rise about double in size.
Now
mix salt,
soda
and
baking
powder with a small amount of remaining flour.
Add to dough.
Finish adding flour to
make a stiff dough (like biscuit dough).
Cover and put in refrigerator
until
ready to
use.
Knead
dough
on floured board.	Cut with biscuit cutter and fold.
Place melted butter in fold.
Bake at 400° until light brown, about 15 minutes.

title: molded shrimp salad
directions: Toss all ingredients, except gelatin and mayonnaise, in a large bowl.
Dissolve gelatin in water and then heat to melt. Mix in mayonnaise and stir gently into shrimp and vegetables. Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: cornbread salad
directions: *I use Martha White Mexican cornbread mix.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat. Add sugar, flour and eggs. Stir well. Add nuts, vanilla and chocolate chips. Pour into greased pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 2 shallow pie crusts.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Mix flour and margarine and mix with buttermilk.
Put the chicken and vegetable mixture in casserole and top with flour mixture.
Cook at 350° for one hour or until brown and bubbly.

title: philadelphia pumpkin swirl cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing on low speed just until blended.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups batter.
Stir remaining 1/4 cup sugar, pumpkin and spices into remaining batter. Spoon 1/2 pumpkin batter over crust; top with spoonfuls of plain batter.
Repeat layers.
Cut through batters with knife several times for marble effect.

title: vegetarian shepherd's pie
directions: Combine mashed potatoes with 2 tablespoons butter, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper, parsley and cream cheese in a large bowl; set aside.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat; saute onions, basil, tarragon and broccoli or zucchini.
Add green pepper, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper to taste.
When vegetables are tender, but not overcooked, set aside.
Add chickpeas and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Heat 1 tablespoon butter in skillet.
Saute mushrooms.
Remove from heat.
Add corn and sour cream.
Layer on top of vegetables, then layer on mashed potatoes, then grated cheese.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°, then uncover and bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until browned a bit on top.
Let sit 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter-oatmeal bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat butter for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and brown sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg, 1/3 cup peanut butter, 1/4 cup milk and vanilla. Beat well.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix until well blended.
Serve with fresh fruit, cake squares or marshmallows as dippers.

title: chuck roast in foil
directions: Place roast on a large piece of aluminum foil and sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Spread celery soup on top.
Wrap in foil and seal well.
Bake in preheated 325° to 350° oven for 20 minutes to 1 hour per pound, or until done.
Slice and pour drippings over roast.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat 3 eggs thoroughly with 2/3 cup sugar, dash of salt, corn syrup and margarine.
Add pecan halves.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool before serving.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Combine evaporated milk with meat.
Divide into 5 patties.
On wax paper, pat each patty into a 5-inch circle.
Put 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each circle.
Draw meat over stuffing and seal.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Turn meat once to brown.

title: wild rice meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well. Firmly press into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 70 minutes. Cover with foil during the last 15 minutes if the top is browning too quickly. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: feather light sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop by teaspoonfuls or feed through a cookie press. Cookies may be sprinkled with sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, stir first 6 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover; chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: pinwheels
