directions: Spray (2 to 3 short sprays) 8 or 9-inch square pan with no stick cooking spray.
Spread on bottom and sides of pan with paper towel.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil 6 medium potatoes.
Cool, peel and grate.
Add 1/3 cup chopped onions.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Heat soup (undiluted); add butter.
Stir in sour cream and pour over the potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle the cheese on top and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix in order given and allow to congeal or set up in refrigerator.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine all.
Put into bottom and up sides of 9 x 13 inch glass baking dish.

title: bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle in layers: graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips, chopped nuts and butterscotch chips.
Pour over the Eagle Brand condensed milk. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: dad's famous fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, crumbs, pepper and seasoning in Ziploc bag and shake to mix.
Mix eggs and milk in large bowl.
Wash chicken and towel dry.
Place in Ziploc with flour mixture; shake.
Take out of Ziploc and place chicken in milk/egg mixture, shake and then replace in flour mixture and shake again.
Heat shortening in large skillet, high heat until melted, then place chicken in shortening.
Lower heat to approximately 350° and cook approximately 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: turkey minute steaks
directions: In shallow bowl, combine bread crumbs, cheese, basil, salt and pepper; mix well.
Dip turkey in egg, then in crumbs, coating both sides.
Melt butter in skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook turkey for 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown and juices run clear.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix with electric mixer, the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and milk.
Blend well and add peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate until firm.
Top with chocolate sauce, Cool Whip and chopped peanuts.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine cauliflower, broccoli, onion, bell pepper and pimento. Toss well.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
(You may double these ingredients.)
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Yields about 8 servings.

title: baklavas (baklava)(makes 40 servings)
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine all ingredients, except lemon juice and honey.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes or until candy thermometer registers 224°.
Add lemon juice and honey; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine butter or margarine and sugar in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in buttermilk.
Mix well. Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Combine tomato paste and water in a saucepan.
Add ground beef and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes, then serve.

title: peach crisp(microwave)
directions: Arrange peaches in an 8-inch square glass dish (microwave-safe).
Melt butter in a small glass bowl in microwave. Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in a bowl.
Add melted butter; mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over peaches.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave for 7 to 8 minutes on High (rotate the dish one-quarter turn once).
Garnish with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: caramel squares
directions: Melt the sugar and butter over low heat. Cool. Add eggs and beat until light. Stir in dry ingredients and beat.
Fold in nuts, dates and vanilla. Spread thinly in a 9
x 13-inch shallow pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Cut in squares before cold.

title: homemade cookies and cream ice cream
directions: Stir ice cream until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip, making sure mixture is creamy.
Crack (do not crumble) Oreo cookies and mix in.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and freeze overnight.

title: brownies
directions: Melt
butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, cocoa, flour, baking powder, vanilla and peanut butter. Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Spread
in
lightly greased pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake in moderate oven
for
30 minutes.
Makes 18 bars or 9 squares.

title: on call appetizers
directions: Slice French bread and halve the slices.
Mix the rest of ingredients and spread on bread.
Broil on foil until brown.

title: beefy vegetable soup
directions: Add all ingredients into microwave-proof casserole.
Cover with lid.
Cook on High for 20 minutes.
Stir.
Cover, cook on (50) for 20 minutes.
Remove and let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Discard bay leaves.
Serves 4 to 6. Cooking time:
40 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: You will need flowers (straw).

title: sugar cookies(100 year old recipe)
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add milk to beaten eggs and beat again.
Add slowly to creamed shortening and sugar. Add flavoring.
Add 2 cups of flour, sifted with baking powder. Add nutmeg.
Add just enough flour to roll easily.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with any fancy shaped cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar or put a raisin or nut in the center of each.
Bake 12 minutes in a hot oven (450°).

title: large broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese.

title: rich pastry shell
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in butter until it is the size of small peas.
Sprinkle with milk.
Mix until it forms a ball.
Roll out to fit a 9-inch pie pan.
Add filling or bake the empty shell at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: praline squares or brown sugar brownies
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan or double recipe and grease a 9 x 13-inch pan or cookie sheet.
Melt shortening over low heat. Remove from heat; blend in egg and brown sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Spread in pan; bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until light touch leaves a slight dent.
Do not overbake.
Cut into squares while warm.
Keeps well in a sealed container.

title: chicken parmesan(microwave recipe)
directions: Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and paprika together in a shallow bowl.
In another shallow dish, beat egg with water.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix together until it looks like cornmeal, don't melt the butter.
Put on top of 1 can sliced peaches (large, 2 1/2 or two 16 ounce).
Sprinkle cinnamon on top, if you like.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Use 9 x 9-inch pan, ungreased.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook uncovered at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate thunder cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan as directed on box.
Let cool 25 to 30 minutes.
Poke holes in cake with wooden spoon handle. Pour on sweetened condensed milk; spread evenly.
Wait 5 minutes. Spread fudge topping over cake.
Wait 5 minutes.
Spread Cool Whip over cake; sprinkle candy bars over the top.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs and milk together and blend with flour.
Remove lid from kettle in which chicken is cooking and drop in rounded tablespoonful of dough over surface, leaving room for dumplings to puff up.
Cover kettle, keeping liquid at a simmer.
Cook for about 15 minutes until dumplings are light and cooked through.
Serve chicken on a large platter surrounded by dumplings.
If you wish, make chicken gravy; serve over chicken and dumplings.

title: holiday ham roll
directions: Mix together onion, green pepper and cream cheese and spread on slices of ham.
Roll ham slices up and secure on toothpick.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat sweet potatoes, sugar, butter, vanilla, eggs and cinnamon together.
Place in greased baking dish.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, water, and salt in a covered dish and bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.
Add soup, onion, and a sprinkle of thyme.
Mix and bake well for 20 minutes longer.

title: easy one-dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, ham and onion powder.
Put in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour evenly over first mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Bake 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Let stand at least 5 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Place in hot tumbler or mug; stir well.
Sprinkle on top freshly ground nutmeg or powdered nutmeg.
Serve at once.

title: heavenly chocolate dessert
directions: Slice banana in thin slices.
Put in cup.
Pour juice over bananas.

title: butter rolls
directions: Roll out one can biscuits.
Cover half of dough with margarine and sugar (quite heavily).
Turn together like fried pie.
Press edges together to seal in sugar and butter.
Cook over medium heat, in butter.
Press flat to make it fry crispy.
Sugar and butter will ooze out for seasoning while cooking.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Measure flour and sift once.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add all ingredients together and sift.
Do not beat with mixer.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; let cool about 30 minutes.
Add drained pineapple, cottage cheese, nuts and Eagle Brand milk; mix well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain.
Stir in pizza sauce, olives, salt, oregano and dash of pepper.
Cook, covered, 30 minutes.
In a bowl, combine egg and cheeses.
Set aside 8 whole tortilla chips. Slightly crush remaining chips.

Spread 1/3 meat mixture in a 13 x 9-inch dish. Top with 1/2 cheese mixture and 1/2 crushed chips. Repeat layers, ending with meat. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Top with whole tortilla chips and more cheese if desired.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crumble Oreos in blender.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese. Prepare pudding.
In a flowerpot (or cake pan), layer ingredients (Oreos, Cool Whip and pudding).
Repeat; end with Oreos on top. Top with a plastic flower!!
Looks real cute made in a sand pail and served with a sand shovel or flowers served with a gardening trowel.

title: tea cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the egg yolk, water and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add the dry ingredients.
Roll, using more flour if necessary.
Cut and brush with egg white.
Bake in a moderate oven about 10 minutes.
Quite rich and crisp.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: In large pan, pour Coke.
Add salt and place chicken in pan. Spoon catsup over chicken.
Cook 40 minutes, turning chicken the last 15 minutes.
(May be cooked on top of stove or in oven.)

title: 3 generation waffle mix
directions: Makes about 8 waffles.

title: old-fashioned baked beans
directions: Sort, clean and wash beans.
Cook, covered, with water until done, approximately 2 hours.
Add water as needed so as not to boil dry.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or at 325° for 2 hours.
These are also very good with just the brown sugar in them.
This recipe doubled, will serve 35 to 50 people.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Let cool.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Sift dry ingredients (set aside).
In a large bowl, beat eggs until thick and light (high speed).
Add sugar, 1/4 cup at a time, beating well after each addition at low speed. Add dry ingredients and mix until smooth.
Add zucchini and nuts with a spoon until well combined.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan on wire rack for 15 minutes.
Remove and ice with Philly cream cheese.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour, salt and baking soda; mix well.
Mix in chocolate chips. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour and alum together in a bowl.
Set aside.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling.
Stir liquids into dry ingredients.
Knead until smooth.
Store in an airtight container.

title: tamales
directions: Brown onion and meat; add seasonings mixed with flour.
Add tomato paste and simmer about 30 minutes.
Cool and shape into tamales about 1 1/2 inches in diameter and 4 inches long.
Mix cornmeal, flour, chili powder and salt together.
Roll shaped tamales in dry mix.
Place each tamale rolled in dry mix on a coffee filter and roll up.
Place tamales in a heavy cooking pot and cover with equal parts of tomato juice and water.
Simmer very slowly for 2 to 3 hours.
Move tamales very gently occasionally to avoid sticking.

title: peach pudding
directions: Combine peaches, water and 1/2 cup sugar in pan.
Bring to boil.
Cream shortening, 1/2 cup sugar, milk, egg and flour.
Put peach mixture in 9 x 9-inch greased baking pan.
Pour other mixture over that.
Bake in 425°
oven until brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Pour in Ro-Tel tomatoes, soup and taco mix.
Heat, then add Velveeta cheese (cut up).
Heat until cheese is melted.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bottom with 1/2 bag of chips, then pour half meat mixture evenly; layer again with chips.
Then top with remaining meat mixture.
Garnish top with a few crumbled chips.
Heat 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve immediately.

title: baked beans
directions: For every can of pork and beans stir in amount given of ketchup, brown sugar, molasses and onion.
Top with bacon slices. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on how dry you like them.
If you like them dry, use a shallow baking dish.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients.
Spread 1/2 cup mixture over each tortilla; roll tortillas jelly roll fashion.
Wrap each separately in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate up to 8 hours.
Cut each roll into 12 slices.
Secure pinwheels with wooden picks.
Serve with salsa.
Yield:
8 dozen.

title: clover honey
directions: Boil sugar and water until it's clear.
Add unburned alum, the size of a cherry.
Boil 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Add clovers and blossoms.
Let stand 10 minutes; strain.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with sugar, salt, syrup and butter.
Add pecan halves.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge of pie crust comes out clean.
Cool before cutting.

title: quick chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler over low heat; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in condensed milk, butter and vanilla.
Blend until butter is mixed with chocolate. Stir in nuts.
Spread mixture immediately into a lightly oiled 8-inch square pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares. Yields 1 1/4 pounds fudge.

title: beefy creamettes
directions: In skillet or saucepan, brown beef and chopped onion, stirring until done.
Cook Creamettes as directed on box.
Combine with tomatoes and Creamettes in saucepan and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crescent, cheese and veggie squares
directions: Use 3/4 cup of the following items: chopped tomatoes, chopped onions, chopped broccoli, shredded carrots, chopped cauliflower and shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: fruit bowl with sherry dressing
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
In top of double boiler, beat egg with cornstarch and add 1/4 cup of syrup.
Whisk in sherry, salt, lemon juice and sugar.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and cool. Fold in sour cream.
Wash and halve strawberries.
Mix with pineapple, orange segments and bananas.
Toss with dressing just before serving in a lettuce-lined bowl.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Sprinkle pecans over bottom of pie shell.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake in slow oven (325°) until golden brown and almost set, about 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: panic!
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Pour pie filling into pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top; pour melted butter over cake mix. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers and onion in jars.
Combine and bring to boil while stirring the sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard seed, celery seed, and turmeric.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Seal and keep in refrigerator.

title: southern persimmon pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add eggs to persimmon pulp, then add dry ingredients, butter and milk.
Add nut meats and mix well.
Bake in a greased dish at 350° until firm, about 1 hour. Serve with hard sauce, if desired.

title: dolly cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set oven at 350°.
Mix together batter ingredients on low speed for about 1 minute.
Beat at higher speed for approximately another minute.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add cream cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour gradually, then flavorings.
Pour into Bundt pan. Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top. Freezes well.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix chicken soup and milk, onion soup, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes.
Top with parsley and butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Put the chicken (whole or in pieces) into a roaster.
Cover it with the unpeeled garlic cloves.
Roast at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
When chicken is done, you can make a white sauce and squeeze the garlic cloves into it for a gravy or just squeeze the cloves onto a piece of bread and eat with the chicken.

title: lentils with pasta
directions: Measure 6 cups cold water into saucepan.
Put lentils in water with 4 cloves of garlic and celery (cut up in small pieces).
Cut slit in garlic cloves, leave whole.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and let simmer 45 minutes until lentils are tender.
Cut pasta into small pieces and cook separately.
Drain and add pasta to cooked lentils.
Add olive oil, salt and pepper to taste.

title: fisherman's casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken, shrimp, mushrooms, onion, wine and butter.
In separate pan, prepare the Rice-A-Roni. Combine in large casserole dish with the browning sauce.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: peaches 'n cream
directions: Blend together the vanilla pudding, baking powder, flour, milk, egg and butter; pour into dish.
Mix together the cream cheese, sugar and juice, then pour on top of other mixture that is in dish. Lay the peaches on top and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until edges are brown.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Beat sugar, salt and eggs together.
Add lard, molasses and 1/2 vinegar milk mix.
Pour rest of vinegar milk mix into separate bowl and add baking soda.
Add alternately with 4 to 5 cups of flour to make batter quite stiff.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drop from floured spoon and bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Nuts may be added to batter.

title: one, two, three, four cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift flour. Add 1/2 cup milk at a time.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, butter to eggs and sugar in separate bowl.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Mix only until blended. Batter will be lumpy.
Spoon in skillet and fry.

title: hearty bean casserole
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown ground beef;
drain.
Add onin, bell pepper and garlic;
cook until tender.
Stir in all of the beans. Combine ketchup, brown sugar, venegar, mustard, salt and pepper; add to bean mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with bacon.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°F. for 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: cheese nacho dip(microwave)
directions: Microwave cheese. Add tomatoes and chilies.
Melt until bubbly. Serve with chips.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Blend well.
Pour in well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Press crescent rolls in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread sausage and sprinkle with cheese and potatoes.
(Note:
May freeze at this point for later use.)
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over the bottom layer.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
(If frozen, be sure to thaw ahead of time or add to baking time.)

title: caramel corn
directions: Spray inside of large paper bag with Pam.
Add popped corn.
In a 1-quart ovenware bowl or measuring cup mix next 4 ingredients. Bring to boil (about 3 1/2 minutes).
Boil about 2 minutes; add soda.
Pour over corn in bag and shake well.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High; shake well.
Pour out on greased foil or cookie sheet.

title: a la simple la orange chicken breast
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Salt and pepper chicken. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
The last 10 to 15 minutes of baking, mix together dry onion soup packet and jar of orange marmalade and spread on top of chicken breasts.
Continue baking another 15 minutes.
Serve with wild rice and mandarin orange salad.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash and drain beets. Leave roots and about 1 inch of stem at tops. Cover with boiling water and cook until tender. Peel and remove stems and roots. Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag. Combine spices, sugar, vinegar, and water in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Add beets; gently boil 5 minutes. Remove spice bag. Place beets into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2 inch headspace. Process in boiling water bath for 30 minutes.

title: chicken divan patsy
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and arrange on bottom of greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with crumbs or almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash cheese souffle
directions: Heat milk and pour over bread crumbs. Add eggs and next 5 ingredients, mixing well. Stir in squash and cheese.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm.

title: waldorf cake
directions: Add vinegar to soda.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste of food color and cocoa, then add buttermilk alternately (also paste with flour and salt, add vinegar and soda, then vanilla).
Do not beat hard, just blend.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in two 9-inch layer pans.
When cool, split each layer, making 4 layers.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: In top of double boiler, blend together Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk, salt and 1 1/2 cups of the water.
Add chocolate. Cook over boiling water, stirring until chocolate melts.
Gradually stir remaining 1/2 cup water into cornstarch, keeping mixture smooth; add gradually, while stirring rapidly, to milk mixture. Continue to cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in vanilla extract.
Turn into individual dishes.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour pork(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole combine the oil, garlic and scallions. Cook on High for 1 minute.
Drain the pineapple chunks, reserving the liquid.
Stir the pineapple chunks and pork into the garlic and scallions.
In a small bowl, stir the reserved pineapple juice, brown sugar, vinegar, and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir into the pork mixture.
Cook on High for 2 to 4 minutes, or until heated through, stirring each minute.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a flat greased casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until you see the casserole bubbling all over.
Remove from oven; then prepare topping.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Spread onions in casserole dish.
Drain beans well; spread over onions.
Spread mushroom soup over top of beans.
Cut cheese into long strips and cover the mushroom soup.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Put all ingredients together and mix.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: eraser(it really works)
directions: Will need wax paper (3 x 6-inch), stapler or tape, saucepan, potholder, rubber spatula and plastic wrap.

title: easy cake
directions: Mix well-beaten eggs with other ingredients; mix well.
Oil and flour tube pan.
Pour in ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Do not stir together, but smooth with back of spoon.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon sauce for pound cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in pot and mix until well blended.
Add boiling
water,
stirring
rapidly
to
prevent lumping.
Cook until thickened
about
10 minutes.
Add butter or margarine.
Cool, then add lemon juice and cream.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar until light.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift
together
dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cheese log
directions: Combine the cheese with the rest of the ingredients.
Form into a long roll and wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm. Serve on a tray surrounded by olives and crackers.

title: congealed spinach salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; chill until slightly congealed. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan or greased mold.
Chill until set.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes; add salt.
Stir in flour and thin out with milk.
Fry on well-greased griddle until brown.
Flip to cook other side until brown.
(Can be made in a blender as well.)

title: ravioli pasta salad
directions: Boil mini ravioli for 20 minutes.
Towel dry.
Add vegetables and toss with Italian dressing.
(If taking to a pot luck, toss with only half the jar of dressing at home and add the remaining dressing when you arrive)

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts about 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove bones and separate breasts into strips.
Allow broccoli to stand at room temperature until thawed.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2 quart rectangular casserole dish.
Arrange broccoli in dish and place chicken on top of it.

title: pizza pie
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Mix with macaroni.
Layer beef and macaroni, pepper and cheese.
End with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Place all ingredients in crock pot early in the morning or the night before and cook on low for at least 8 hours.
Add one chopped green pepper if desired after 4 hours.
Take meat out of juice and break up in very small pieces.
Return to juice and mix.
Serve on warm buns.
Makes about 8 sandwiches.
Do not add water to meat. Unused portions can be frozen.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine ingredients; mix lightly.
Pour in pie crusts. Refrigerate.

title: oven fried zucchini(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Spray nonstick cookie sheet liberally with cooking spray.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, garlic powder and pepper on sheet of waxed paper and set aside.
Quarter zucchini lengthwise, then cut each spear in half or thirds.
Put in plastic bag; add oil and water.
Close bag and shake to coat spears.
Roll each spear in crumb mixture until lightly coated. Arrange spears on cookie sheet in single layer.
Bake in a 475° oven for 6 minutes and then broil for 1 minute until spears are lightly browned and tender-crunchy.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put in bowl in order given and mix well with mixer.
Bake in a 365° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use 13 x 9-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Can be made in two 9-inch layers also.
Makes a very moist cake.
Frost with chocolate or vanilla icing.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well by hand, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan upside-down coffee cake
directions: Mix pecans, corn syrup and margarine.
Pour into ungreased round pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inch.
Spread to cover bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; beat 30 seconds.
Spread over pecan mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Run knife around edge of pan to loosen.
Immediately place on heatproof plate.

title: banana cream dessert
directions: Blend butter, flour and pecans.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes or until slightly browned in 350° oven.
Cool. Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar; fold in whipped topping.
Spread on crust.
Slice bananas on mixture.
Mix pudding with milk; spread over bananas.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish with a few chopped nuts.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain all beans, then combine.
Place alternate layers of beans, onion and pepper in salad bowl.

title: yogurt
directions: Better if mixed the night before.
Mix all ingredients together.
Equals 1 milk and 1 fruit.

title: turtle bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Set aside.
In bowl combine remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk and dry cake mix. Press half of mixture in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 cup nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread caramel mixture carefully over nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop remaining cake mix by teaspoons over caramel and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange candy cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oleo and eggs.
Sift together flour and soda.
(Use three cups in batter and reserve 1 cup for dusting candy, nuts and dates.)
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Dust candy, nuts and dates with remaining 1 cup flour.
Add to batter with grated orange rind.
Mix well.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add strawberries with lite sugar.
Stir until Jell-O mixture starts to gel; then add Cool Whip.
Stir until well blended.
Pour mixture into graham cracker pie crust.
Chill.

title: berry banana smoothie
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Makes 2 (1 cup) servings.

title: beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir meat until brown.
Drain off fat.
Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
In ungreased 2-quart casserole, mix all the ingredients except potato chips. Cover; bake 40 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with potato chips and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Sift together the remaining ingredients.
Make dough and chill. Roll into balls the size of walnuts (1 teaspoonful). Roll ball in a mixture of 2 tablespoons each sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: rice with apples
directions: Cook rice in milk until tender.
Pare and slice enough tart apples to make a pint.
Butter a pudding dish, put in a layer of rice, the apples and cover with the remainder of the rice.
Cover and bake 20 minutes, then uncover.
Dot with bits of butter and brown the top.
Serve with cream and sugar.

title: grandma zita's chili(serves 8)
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion.
May add small green pepper, if desired.
Put in remaining ingredients in Dutch oven.
Slow simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Good for crock-pots.

title: butterscotch cookies(makes about 12 dozen)
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla gradually.
Add flour.
Stir in butterscotch morsels
and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Fold in one package of coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spinach madelyn
directions: Cook spinach according to package (do not add salt). Drain and reserve liquid. Melt butter in saucepan on low heat. Add flour and stir until smooth. Add onion and cook until tender, but not brown. Add evaporated milk and veggie liquid, stirring constantly, and cook until smooth and thick. Add seasonings and cheese which has been cut into small pieces. Stir until melted and combine with spinach. Place in small, buttered casserole dish. Crumble Ritz crackers with butter for topping. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese bits
directions: Beat oleo until soft and smooth.
Mix all ingredients together; form into marble size balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and press with a fork.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes. Do not brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and chill for 1 hour.
Top with cherries if desired.

title: yum yum brownies
directions: Bring
margarine,
oil,
cocoa	and water to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: In large pot, simmer lentils, water and salt.
Cover 3 to 4 hours.
Add garlic, onion, celery and carrots and simmer another hour.
About 30 minutes before serving, add tomatoes, wine, lemon juice and black pepper.
Season to taste.
Enjoy.
Serve with bread or rolls.

title: apple "dump" cake
directions: Spray oblong dish with Pam.
Set oven to 350°.
Dump crushed pineapple, juice and all, into dish.
Next, spoon apple pie filling on top of pineapple.
Then spread dry cake mix on top of apple, crushing lumps in cake mix.
Then gently pour melted margarine/butter on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm.
Extra garnish with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: tomato relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour vinegar over mixture. Let flavors blend at least 1 hour.
Delicious when eaten with black-eyed peas or collard greens.

title: coronado casserole
directions: Cook beef, rice and onion in 1 tablespoon oil until lightly browned.
Season.
Add sliced olives, tomato juice and boiling water.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover; spread with cheese.
Continue baking for about 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
(Supposed to serve 6.)

title: apple-raisin stuffed chops
directions: Cut pocket in chops
along
the
bone.	Pour
milk over bread crumbs.
Stir in
apples,
raisins,
salt,	the sage and melted butter.
Stuff each chop with about 1/4 cup of filling. Brown chops in shortening
or
oil.
Pour oil off when browned and season with pepper and salt.
Cover tightly and simmer for 45 minutes to an hour.
Serves 6.

title: pork tenderloin roast florentina
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Trim excess fat from pork.
Make a deep slit the length of the tenderloin, without cutting all the way through.
Mince garlic and rosemary together.
Press half of it into slit of meat; close the slit.
Starting with larger end, tightly roll up tenderloin and secure with a string.
Place in small shallow roasting pan.
Combine remaining garlic-rosemary with lemon juice, cloves, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Reduce oven temperature to 425°.
Brush the roast with remaining garlic mixture.
Pour the broth into roasting pan.
Baste every 15 minutes.
Cook until barely pink, 30 to 40 minutes.
When done, let meat sit 5 minutes before carving.
Serves 2.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with 3 tablespoons butter over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Cream remaining butter with cheese. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar; cream well after each addition. Blend in 1 egg, 1 teaspoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Set aside.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Makes 2 pies.
Freezes well.

title: pork chops and peaches
directions: Rub pork chops with soy sauce.
Sprinkle with black pepper. Blanch, peel and slice peaches in crescents (canned peaches may be used).
Sprinkle with lemon juice to prevent browning.
Heat butter in frypan large enough to handle chops.
Brown chops on both sides. Lower heat and cook for 10 minutes.
Turn over.
Cook another 10 minutes.
Add peaches and wine and cook for 5 more minutes.
Serve at once.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended and smooth.
Serve on crackers or toast points.

title: biscuits supreme mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Store in airtight container.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9x13-inch pan.
Spread undrained pineapple and pie filling evenly in pan.
Spread dry cake mix evenly over fruit. Top with nuts.
Drizzle melted butter over the mixture.

title: chicken lattice
directions: Combine potato soup, milk, chicken, 1 cup cheese, 1/2 can fried onions and veggies.
Spread into baking dish, 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: cinnamon swirl breakfast muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease or place muffin cups into muffin pan.
Combine quick bread mix (large clear packet), water, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Beat with spoon until well blended.
Then place blended mixture into muffin cups (2 to 3 tablespoons of the mixture per muffin).
Sprinkle cinnamon mixture over each muffin (about 1 teaspoon to 1 tablespoon per muffin).
Sprinkle a heaping teaspoon of mini chocolate chips over each muffin and then stir with the end of a spoon in each muffin (just to give it a swirled effect).
Bake in oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool on metal rack (or just cool for a few minutes, then remove from muffin pan).
Store in sealed container for up to a week, maybe two if refrigerated.	These are great, so they probably won't last for even a week!

title: addie's chicken stew
directions: Put water and salt in a pan.
Add chicken and gently boil until tender.
Remove chicken from water and cool.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix together and spread on muffins.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes. Cut to bite size pieces.

title: salami kabobs
directions: On each of 16 toothpicks, string an olive, a salami slice (folded in quarters), then a pineapple chunk.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 16 kabobs.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in a small pan.
Boil rice as directed.
Mix broccoli and rice together. Add soups and milk.
Put Cheez Whiz on top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in 400° oven.

title: working woman biscuits
directions: Put yeast into water and let stand awhile.
Mix rest of the ingredients.
Add to water and yeast and mix.
These can be sealed and stored in refrigerator and used as desired.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine 1 cup granulated sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in milk.
Bring to a boil and cool until thick.
Blend small amount of hot mixture into slightly beaten eggs.
Add all egg mixture to cooked mixture.
Cook and stir until thick.
Remove from
heat.
Add butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Mix well. Cover and cool.
Fold in sour cream and spoon into baked pie shell.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix
all
ingredients thoroughly.
Boil for 15 minutes. Pour into
sterilized
jars to within 1/2 inch of top.
Put on cap; screw
band firmly tight.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Yields 4 half pints.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss together last three ingredients for the dressing.
Toss in dry ingredients.

title: banana loaf or muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry mixture, stirring until moistened.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: breakfast shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor.
Mix on blend to milk-shake consistency.
Drink immediately.

title: seven layer vegetable salad
directions: Place bacon in a large, deep skillet.
Cook over medium high heat until evenly brown.
Drain and set aside.
In a 9 x13 inch pan layer the lettuce followed by the peas, green pepper, bacon, cauliflower and celery.
In a small bowl combine the mayonnaise and the sugar.
Spread mixture over salad.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover and chill for at least 8 to 12 hours before serving.

title: chocolate and peanut butter bars
directions: Combine peanut butter and butter; add sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Add flour, salt and 1 cup chocolate chips. Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle extra chips on top.
Let stand 5 minutes and spread.

title: oatmeal wafers
directions: Cream white sugar, brown sugar and margarine.
Add soda and hot water.
Mix with sugar and margarine.
Add flour, oatmeal, salt and vanilla.
Drop 1/2 to 1 teaspoon of dough on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well; spoon into a 2-quart casserole dish.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Pour chocolate into saucepan and cover with 2 inches of hot tap water.
Cover with lid and let stand 3 to 5 minutes. Chocolate should be soft.
Drain off water.
Add the egg yolks; stir with a whisk and cook over low heat until it thickens. Remove from the heat.
Add the butter, vanilla and brandy.
Set aside to cool.
Beat the egg whites until they form soft peaks. Add sugar slowly while beating with electric mixer at high setting.
Keep beating until stiff peaks are formed.
Take 1/4 egg mixture and put into the cooled chocolate mixture.
Mix well.
Fold the remaining egg whites into the chocolate mixture.
Pour into individual dishes.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening; blend and cool.
Add sugar and egg.
Sprinkle yeast in warm water and stir until dissolved. Add to mixture.
Add flour and blend well, beating after each cup. Cover and put in refrigerator.

title: broccoli raisin salad
directions: Note:
Peeled broccoli stems may be used, also.

title: broccoli parmesan
directions: Wash broccoli and peel tough stems; steam broccoli 10 minutes. Meanwhile, heat olive oil and garlic 3 to 4 minutes, then pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and lemon juice.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Mix well first 4 ingredients; add flour.
Drop by tablespoon into 1/2-inch oil.
Cook until brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to the sugar and egg mixture.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan over low heat.
Add cocoa, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat; set aside. Combine milk and brown sugar and heat.
Combine confectioners sugar and milk mixture in large mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth. Add warm chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed until smooth and slightly thickened, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool at room temperature to spreading consistency (about 1/2 hour). Makes 3 cups.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and salt; set aside.
Beat together eggs, pumpkin, sugar and oil.
Add flour mixture and beat well.
Stir in pecans.

title: best-ever bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the water.
Stir in everything except the flour.
Mix well.
Stir in half the flour at first, then add enough to make it easy to handle.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Use however much you need; place remaining dough in greased bowl and turn the dough greased side up.
Cover and store no longer than 5 days.

title: pineapple bar
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a jelly roll pan 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: purple poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then poke with fork at 1/2 inch intervals.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water. Pour over cake in pan.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: old fashioned ginger bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together quickly.
Pour into medium sized baking pan that has been rubbed with butter and dusted with flour. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Add other 2 liquid ingredients.
Add dry ingredients.
Let rise for 2 hours, or put in cold oven.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Dough can be kept in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, eggs, sour cream and oil.
Spread 1/2-inch in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over cake mixture.
Spread other half of cake mixture in pan and swirl with knife.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and sugars thoroughly.
Add egg and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Then stir into butter mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Let mixture come to boil.
Turn fire to low and let simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove.
Add peanut butter and beat until ready to pour.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: gourmet cheese potatoes
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add cheese and milk; pour over shredded potatoes.
Top with buttered bread cubes. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chipped beef casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over beef; let stand 5 minutes and drain. Stir soup until creamy.
Add milk, cheese, onion, uncooked macaroni and beef.
Add eggs and mix gently.
Turn into a 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Store, covered, overnight in refrigerator. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: athenian chicken
directions: Place chicken in a shallow baking dish.
Add oil, lemon juice, garlic, oregano and pepper.
Toss chicken with seasonings; cover and marinate, refrigerated, for at least 1/2 hour.
Grill or broil chicken 6 to 8 inches from heat source for 15 minutes, turning 2 to 3 times.
Place Feta slices on top of chicken; continue to cook for 3 to 5 minutes, until cheese softens and chicken is cooked through.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups water (1 hot and 1 cold) plus the juice from the berries.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.
Whip cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Spread on top of the salad and place back in refrigerator.

title: easy bake enchiladas
directions: Mix picante sauce and enchilada sauce together and set aside. Brown hamburger with onions and drain.
Add beans to hamburger. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam spray.
Spoon just 2 to 3 tablespoons of picante/enchilada sauce in pan.

Take tortilla shells and fill with hamburger and bean mixture, about 1/2 cup. Roll tortillas and place into pan lengthwise next to each other. Pour picante sauce mixture over tortillas covering all of them. Top with sour cream, Cheddar cheese and black olives.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serves easily 10 to 12 people.
Great served with nacho chips on the side (or on top).

title: meat loaf
directions: Put a pound of hamburger meat in large bowl with onion, salt, pepper, 1 or 1/2 package crackers.
Work the crackers up fine.
Add the tomato sauce.
Work all together.
Get you a pan or a bowl that will work well with this to go in the oven.
You may use garlic powder if you like.
Get oven hot 350°.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break cake into small pieces in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish or close to that size.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cut strawberries into small pieces or you can mash them up.
Add to jello.
Pour over cake and mix well.
Mix pudding by directions on box and spread over cake.
After the pudding has set, spread Cool Whip on top.
Serves about 24, depending on size of blocks you cut.

title: chocolate fudge or peanut butter
directions: Combine sugar, oleomargarine, marshmallows and cream.
Cook mixture for
seven minutes after it starts boiling.
Take off heat and add vanilla and peanut butter or chocolate chips.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake the cake mix.
After cake mix is baked and cooled, poke holes in cake with wooden spoon handle 2-inches apart.
Shake cream of coconut well and pour over cake and into holes.
Mix coconut
with the Cool Whip and spread over cake.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine butter, Crisco and sugar. Cream together well. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well. Add flour, buttermilk, soda, coconut and nuts. Whip 5 egg whites and fold in. Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch sheet cake pan or 3 layer pans.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions; cool.
Punch holes in brownies with a fork and pour Kahlua over brownies; set aside.

title: squash dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish. Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased dish. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Coarsely grind together apples and cranberries.
Add sugar. Mix and let stand overnight.
Mix Jell-O, which has been dissolved in hot water, with pecans and marshmallows.
Add all to cranberry mixture.
Return to refrigerator and let set.

title: herbed spinach bake
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well, squeezing out excess liquid.
Combine spinach with remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes more or until set.

title: apple-rice salad
directions: Combine cooked rice,
pineapple, marshmallows and sugar in a bowl.
Toss gently to
mix and refrigerate 3 hours.
Fold in apples, cherries and
dates.
Then	fold
in whipped cream. Chill 1 more hour.
Yield:
18 servings.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix everything together except the butter and corn flakes. Place in casserole dish.
Pat crushed corn flakes on top of potato mixture.
Pour melted butter over corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Tastes even better when reheated.

title: lemon chiffon pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Cream together butter or oleo and flour mixture.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; add to milk.
Gradually add lemon juice and rind.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in carefully to other mixtures.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Place in pan with 1-inch of hot water.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple pecan loaf
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Cream butter. Blend in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients alternately with pineapple juice and vanilla.
Fold in pecans.
Bake approximately 1 1/4 hours at 350° (glass pan at 325°).

title: pot roast chicken
directions: Clean, stuff and tie chicken.
Season, flour lightly and brown in fat in Dutch oven.
Place onions around chicken.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover and cook until tender, putting potatoes in the last hour.
Serves 6.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Set aside. Melt butter and sugar. Let cool. Combine milk, salt and water. Add to butter and sugar. Add 1/2 cup of the flour at a time. Mix dough until you can stretch. Let dough rise. Fry.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together well.
Add sweet milk.
Fold in beaten whites of eggs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: japanese fruitcake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition. Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Stir in vanilla.
Divide batter in 1/2; stir spices, raisins and pecans into one portion.
Pour plain batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans and spiced batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool on wire racks.
Prick layers and spread layers, top and sides with Japanese Frosting, layers with a light layer on top of spice layer.

title: poor man's lasagna
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions, but don't get it quite done; then, starting with spaghetti sauce, alternately layer the sauce, macaroni and cheese, ending with cheese, in a baking pan. Cover entire top with pepperoni.
Heat in a 375° oven for approximately 15 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon in a large plastic bag. Cut each biscuit into quarters and add to bag.
Shake to coat biscuits evenly.
Place in greased Bundt pan.
Melt margarine and brown sugar in small pan. Add 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp stuffed peppers
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Cut off tops of peppers;
remove seeds and membrane.
Precook in salted water 5 minutes; drain. Cook celery
in	butter.
Stir
in
flour,
seasoned salt and basil. Add
milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until thick. Add 1/4 cup cheese and wine; stir until cheese melts.
Stir in shrimp
and macaroni.
Bake
at
for
30	minutes.
Add remaining cheese (1/2 cup) atop peppers.
Bake 3 minutes more.

title: high-top muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt and mix thoroughly.
Make a well in center; pour in buttermilk, oil and egg.
Immediately stir with fork just until dry ingredients are moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Spoon into 6 greased 3 x 1 1/4-inch muffin cups (1/2 cup capacity), filling to the rim.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 large muffins.

title: fish and cheese chowder
directions: Cut fish into 1-inch cubes. Cook onion, carrot and celery in butter until onion is transparent. Blend in flour, salt and paprika. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add broth and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add fish; simmer until fish flakes easily (5 minutes). Add cheese and stir until melted. Yield:
2 1/2 quarts.

title: red, white and blue salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package of raspberry jello in 2 cups hot water and pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until set.

title: potato soup
directions: In large pot, cook potatoes in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Set potatoes aside.

title: moist 'n chewy brownies
directions: Melt chips and butter.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken and mushroom medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix carrots and rice in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix water/wine and both soups in a small bowl.
Add half of this mixture to the carrots and rice.
Mix thoroughly. Place chicken on top of rice mixture and add sliced mushrooms. Cover with remaining water/wine mixture.
Seal tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours.
Twenty minutes preparation time and 75 minutes baking time.

title: earl's birthday cake(1 step)
directions: Bake cake as per directions on box.
Add Cool Whip for frosting.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain fruit well in colander and toss gently.
Mix together the sour cream, coconut and marshmallows.
Mix together carefully. Garnish with coconut and cherries.
Chill.
Very good!

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together; chill.
Dip for celery, cauliflower, etc.

title: ambrosia fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix fruit and juices in a bowl.
Spoon into individual bowls and sprinkle coconut on it.

title: lentil and squash soup
directions: Combine broth and all ingredients in large saucepan.
Simmer until vegetables and lentils are tender, stirring occasionally, about 45 minutes.
Then soup with extra broth if necessary. Season with salt and pepper.

title: artichoke and tomato pasta
directions: Drain artichokes of juice.
Add juice to stir-fry pan tomatoes, garlic, basil and chopped artichokes.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Toss with linguini or angel hair pasta and top with fresh grated Parmesan cheese.

title: rigatoni
directions: Cook rigatoni as directed on package; drain.
Cook hamburger in large pot until done.
Add chopped onion and garlic; cook for 5 minutes.
Add Ragu, tomato paste and water.
Cook for 15 minutes. Makes 2 large pans.

title: lots o'apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts; beat at low speed until moistened.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Serve warm or cool with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat together eggs, flour and sugar.
Mix the rest together and pour in slightly greased casserole dish.
(You can use a little of the bacon grease to grease the dish.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Well, what can I say.
Corn is always good but add cheese and bacon and it's great.

title: fruit dip deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Chill.
Prepare fresh or frozen fruit.
Dip or mix with fresh or frozen fruit.
Can be prepared 24 hours before serving time.
Makes 1 1/2 cups dip.

title: potato stuffing
directions: Saute chopped onions and chopped celery in oil until golden brown.
Crush crackers, wet and squeeze.
Crumble into onions and celery.
Follow directions on potato pancake mix.
Add 2 extra eggs to potato pancake mix.
Add onions, celery and crackers with paprika, garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well together.

title: chilled corn chowder with cilantro
directions: Combine 3 cups of the corn, the green chilies, and 1 cup of chicken broth in blender or food processor.
Whirl 2 minutes or until smooth.
Pour corn puree mixture into medium size saucepan. Add remaining corn.
Dissolve dry milk powder in remaining broth; stir into saucepan.
Bring to boiling over medium heat.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Stir in salt, pepper and cilantro.
Transfer to bowl.
Chill the chowder, covered, for 4 hours or overnight before serving.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy, beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift cocoa with flour, baking powder and salt.
Work into creamed mixture.
Spoon into gresaed 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta. Cool. Add salt and pepper. Add onion and cucumber. Mix in the amount of slaw dressing that you like.
Add cheese. Mix.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Bake until tender at 350°.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat again until fluffy.
Gradually add flour until dough is soft and smooth.
Pat dough in jelly roll pan or 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 hour or until golden.
Remove from oven and cut in squares.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar, if desired.
Let cool in pan and store in airtight container.
Makes about 36 squares.
Do not use oleo.
It won't work!!

title: grandpa's olive recipe
directions: You will need a 5 gallon crock, either stainless steel, wooden or pottery.

title: quick wacky chocolate cake
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan for single, 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for double recipe.
(To double recipe, double all ingredients.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Chop onions and celery and saute in oleo.
Add other ingredients.
Mix with broccoli in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: turkey breast
directions: Combine all ingredients except turkey, in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Place turkey breast in a 13 x 9-inch oiled baking dish.
Pour 1/2 the mixture over the turkey; cover with foil and bake about an hour.
Pour the other 1/2 over the turkey and continue baking another hour.
Check for doneness.

title: pork chops and sauce
directions: Brown pork chops; drain.
Heat soup, sour cream and Milnot in saucepan.
Add a little water if it's too thick.
Put pork chops in baking dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Pour soup mixture over chops.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Delicious served with mashed potatoes.

title: veggie party treat
directions: Prepare corn muffin mix as directed on box.
Bake in a 10-inch flan pan.
Cool and remove to serving tray.
Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry salad dressing mix.
Spread on cooled corn bread.
Top with chopped vegetables and cheese.

title: shrimp cheese spread (dip)
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and spread on tray (pizza size).
Pour 1/2 bottle chili sauce on top, then spread on shrimp. Refrigerate and serve with crackers.
You can prepare early in day for evening.
Just cover and chill.

title: tangolini
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef in big skillet.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Add all ingredients to meat, noodles and cheese last.
Mix well and bake in casserole dishes about 45 minutes at 350°.
Toasted almonds or mushrooms or both can be added before baking.
Serves 10.

title: red hot applesauce
directions: Peel, core and quarter apples.
Place apples, sugar, water and candies in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook until apples are soft but still chunky.
Cool.
Serve cold or at room temperature.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and lard together well with hands.
Drop egg in a cup with the vinegar and fill the cup with water. Beat and mix into flour mixture.

title: oven-fried chicken normandy
directions: Melt the margarine; put 3 tablespoons of it into a dish and blend in the mustard.
Wash, cut and dry the potatoes.
Cut into wedges and coat with the remaining margarine.
Place in a large baking pan.
Place a rack over the potatoes.
Coat chicken with margarine mixture, then the crumbs, shaking off excess.
Arrange, skin side up, on the rack.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until meat of thighs is no longer pink when tested.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat together the cream cheese and juice until well blended. Gradually add sugar and milk, beating until well blended.
Makes 1 cup frosting.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in crock jar or large kettle.
Pour scalding hot salt water over them.
Let stand 3 days.
Pour off water and slice cucumbers thin.
Soak in alum water.
Let stand 3 hours. Drain and make a syrup of 3 sugar and vinegar.
Cook syrup and boil 1 minute.
Pour over cucumbers in crock jar or large kettle.
Let stand 24 hours.
Pour off heated syrup and again pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
The third time heat syrup and add ground cloves, celery seed and ground cinnamon.
Pack cucumbers into jars.
Pour hot syrup over them.
Seal.
Ready to use in 6 weeks.

title: hot peppered shrimp
directions: In a mixer bowl or food processor, beat margarine until light. Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp, and beat until well blended.
Store butter in refrigerator and use as needed.

title: seasoning salt
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in a sealed jar.
Makes 1/3 cup.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Set pineapple aside.
In saucepan, combine juice, sugar, eggs and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium-low heat until slightly thickened.
Remove and cool.
Stir in pineapple, celery, apples and pecans.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: nut cups
directions: Blend above ingredients and form into 1-inch balls, grease "nut cup pans" well and form cups with dough.
(Nut cup pans are smaller than muffin pans).

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, sugar and vanilla.
Place 1 scant tablespoon cooked rice in the bottom of each of 8 custard cups.
(We used an 8-inch glass cake plate.)
Fill with egg mixture.
Place cups in a pan of water (you don't have to put the pie plate in water) and bake at 375° about 30 minutes (30 to 35 for cake plate).
Do not over bake.
Cool; turn into serving dishes and top with vanilla sauce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix lightly but well.
Mix dry ingredients and add to egg mixture. (Add nuts optional.)
Bake 1 hour in two greased and floured loaf pans.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: danish shortbread cookies
directions: Knead and shape into 1 1/2-inch rolls.
Chill overnight. Slice and sprinkle with sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, until light brown.

title: mexican chicken bake
directions: Mix the chicken, onions, green pepper, soup and Tabasco.
Fold in the corn chips.
Place in a shallow baking pan about, 9 x 12-inches in size.
Spread grated cheese over the top.
Place in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until the cheese is melted.
Serve at once, piping hot.
Serves 6.

title: bacon potato chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, cook bacon over medium heat until browned.
Add onions and continue cooking until tender (2 to 3 minutes); drain.
Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Continue cooking until potatoes are tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Reduce heat to low and stir in soup, sour cream and milk.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until heated through (3 to 5 minutes). Season to taste.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Place cinnamon and mulling spice in coffee container in electric coffee pot.
Pour cider in pot and heat thoroughly. Serve hot!

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: raspberry ice cream
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar to dissolve.
Add frozen berries; squish and break up any clumps of berries.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Crank until frozen.

title: basil bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan. Let dough thaw. Place in Bundt pan. Pour butter, basil, parsley, green onions and garlic over the dough. Cover with plastic wrap and a towel. Let rise for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sky high biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Cut in butter. Add egg and milk, stirring quickly and briefly.
Knead lightly on floured board. Roll or pat gently to 1-inch thickness. Cut into biscuits with cutter dipped in flour.
Place in greased 9-inch pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: corn and shrimp chowder
directions: Put stock, milk, potatoes and corn in large pot, bring to boil and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: Scald milk and butter over low heat.
Mix bread cubes, raisins and nuts in an 8-inch glass baking dish.
Beat together milk mixture, sugar, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour over bread. Microwave on Bake-7 (Medium) for 12 to 14 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yield:
One 8 x 8-inch dish.

title: pepper steak
directions: In a large skillet, heat cooking oil.
Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Brown steak, bell pepper and onion (onion and bell pepper cut into large pieces, not finely chopped).
Reduce heat; add crushed tomatoes, tomato paste and seasoning to taste.
Stir well.
Cover and simmer for approximately 1 hour or until steak is tender.

title: carrot-broccoli casserole(microwave)
directions: Place broccoli in package on microproof plate and put in microwave oven. Cook on High for 4 minutes. Remove from oven and set aside. Combine soup, carrots, sour cream, flour, onion, salt and pepper in 1 1/2-quart microproof casserole.
Cut broccoli into 1-inch pieces. Stir into soup mixture. Cover and cook on High for 6 minutes. Remove from oven. Stir and set aside.
Place butter in 2-cup glass measure.
Cook on High for 1 minute. Remove from oven. Add stuffing cubes to butter and blend well. Spoon over broccoli mixture.
Place in microwave and cook on High for 6 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: eight cup fruit salad
directions: Drain cherries and oranges.
Mix well with other ingredients and chill overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; take from bone.
Melt margarine in bottom of baking dish.
Mix broth from chicken with dressing (leave enough dry dressing mix to sprinkle on top).
Mix soups and water.
In baking dish, put layer of dressing mix, layer of chicken.
Pour soup mixture over dressing and chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing crumbs on top.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Cook egg, flour, sugar and pineapple juice; beat and cook until thick.
Let cool.
Add Dream Whip and spread over jello.

title: strawberry whatizit
directions: Mix pretzel crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and melted margarine. Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes. Cool thoroughly.

title: boston baked corn
directions: Combine mustard, salt, brown sugar and catsup.
Add onion and corn.
Mix.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with bacon. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Let set overnight. The next day, boil for 20 minutes. Add 1 large strawberry or raspberry Jell-O.
Pour in jars and seal. Makes approximately 10 (8 ounce) jars.

title: cool whip pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together margarine and sugar. Sift flour before measuring.
Add flour and eggs alternately to batter, starting and ending with flour.
Fold in flavorings and whipped topping.
Mix only until blended.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: creamy peanut pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate with aluminum foil; set aside.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add coconut, stir occasionally until lightly toasted.
Blend in 1 cup peanut butter chips, stir until morsels melt and mixture is combined.
Press evenly on bottom and sides (not over rim) of foil-lined pie plate.
Chill in refrigerator until firm, about 45 minutes.
Remove foil and place back into pie plate.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Mix jello with 4 cups boiling water.
Blend in partially thawed strawberries.
Let thicken.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Pour over cake.

title: rolled chicken breast florentine
directions: With meat mallet or rolling pin, pound chicken to 1/4 inch thickness.
Place a ham slice, cheese slice and 1/4 of the spinach on each piece of chicken.
Roll up chicken from short end, jelly roll fashion.
Secure with wooden tooth pick.
Place chicken, seam side down, in 12 x 8 microwave safe dish.
Cover with vented plastic wrap. microwave on high 5 minutes.
In a small bowl, stir soup until smooth, stir in onion, water and thyme.
Pour over chicken, cover, microwave on high 10 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear, rotating dish once during cooking. Let stand covered 5 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Melt cheese.
Add cooked ground beef (drained).
Add chili. Heat until warm.
Serve with chips.

title: lemon sauce cooked
directions: Mix thoroughly and cook over low heat until slightly thick.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Heat shortening and cocoa until melted.
Stir in sugar and milk and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add flour, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Stir quickly until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Blend at low speed of electric mixer just to moisten; scrape sides of bowl. Then beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into a 10-inch tube pan which has been lined on bottom with paper.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until cake tester inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 15 minutes.
Loosen from sides and remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly on rack.

title: la casa casserole
directions: Brown onion and beef. Drain.
Add oil and tortillas.
Heat together.
Add sauces and 2 cups cheese.
Mix well.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with remaining cheese. Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pepperoni stuffed pizza
directions: Combine flour, yeast and salt, mix well.
Stir in hot water and oil.
Turn out on a floured surface and knead 1 minute.
Let rise 5 minutes.
Cut into 2 portions, 1 slightly larger.
Place larger in a well-greased 10-inch spring-form pan.
Overlap slices of pepperoni to cover dough in pan (use 1/2 of pepperoni).
Sprinkle cheese evenly.
Top with rest of pepperoni.
Pat out rest of dough to make circle large enough to fit pan.
Put over pepperoni and fold edges back.
Brush edges with water and pinch to make a curb. Slash a few holes to let steam escape.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Take out and put on a baking sheet. Pour sauce over top and bake until sauce begins to bubble (8 minutes).

title: orange cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat at medium speed for 5 minutes. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: weight watchers soup
directions: Fry beef; drain.
Combine all the other ingredients, except macaroni; bring to full boil.
Add ground beef; cook 1/2 hour. Add macaroni.
Turn on low and let simmer.
Makes a large kettle of soup.

title: raspberry-orange pops
directions: Put the pink salt in a glass, then put milk in it, then stir it and drink.

title: grandmother lou's pound cake
directions: Cream butter with mixer; gradually add sugar and eggs one at a time, beating after each. Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour. Stir in flavor; pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until the toothpick comes out clean. Makes 3 loaves.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and roll them into little balls. Bake at 350° until light brown. Remove them from the oven and let them cool.
Roll them in confectioners sugar.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 1 1/2 minutes.
Set off stove.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix and drop on wax paper.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix pudding, Jell-O and water in a medium saucepan over medium-high heat.
Bring to a boil.
Stir rapidly for 1 minute. Place in refrigerator to cool about 10 minutes.
Stir; place back in refrigerator for 5 minutes (do not set).
Line the bottom of graham cracker pie crust with fresh strawberries (sliced in half). Pour mixture over strawberries.
Chill for 2 hours before serving. Serve with whipped cream.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk; bring to boil and cook 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese on ham.
Then spread horseradish. Sprinkle with Accent and roll.
Cut into bite-size pieces.

title: holiday ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix together cheeses, ham, onions, and green chilies.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped walnuts.

title: turkey dressing - squares
directions: Mix dressing and soup with 1 can warm water.
Add margarine, celery, onion and egg; mix well.
Spread in greased baking pan and bake at 350° until brown.
Cut in squares.
Serve with turkey and gravy.

title: stretch me punch
directions: Add enough water to make two gallons.
This punch is very sweet.
Add more water or a lot of ice.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add pineapple and fold mixture with bread cubes.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.
Great served with ham.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Dip skinned, deboned chicken in the sour cream, coating well. Then press the chicken into the potato chips until entire chicken is well-covered.

title: tennessee sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water.
Drain pineapple (save juice).
Add bananas and pineapple.
Mix in jello.
Place marshmallows on top and chill until firm.

title: most popular potato casserole
directions: Let hash browns thaw and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix butter, cheese, soup, sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: crock-pot spanish rice
directions: Mix all together in crock-pot.
Cook 6 to 7 hours on low.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Steam lightly; brown celery and onion in butter.
Add soup, broth, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce, chicken and salt. Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into buttered dish.
Top with noodles and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rolled molasses cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix next 2 ingredients together and add.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Add cream of tartar.
Add flour last.
Bake at 375°.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Measure and sift into a large bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well and add the oil, egg yolks, cold water and vanilla.
Beat with a spoon until smooth.
Beat the egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Pour yolk mixture over white mixture and beat until blended well. Pour into ungreased tube pan. Bake 55 minutes at 325° and then 10 minutes at 350°. Cool in pan turned upside down.
Remove and frost.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Add nectar, oil and lemon extract to cake mix and blend well. Add eggs, one
at
a
time,
beating
well	after
each addition. Pour into
well-greased
tube pan.	Bake 50 minutes at 350°. While hot,	punch
holes
in cake with fork and pour glaze over it.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine flour, oats, wheat germ, nuts, sugar and cinnamon. Work in butter to form crumb topping.

title: green bean and mozzarella salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Cover.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: eggnog
directions: Combine egg with sugar and salt. Add milk and vanilla. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Serve hot or cold.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco mix, beans and water. Let cook on low while you prepare other ingredients.
Make up rice and prepare lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
Salads are layered on each plate as follows:
corn chips, meat mixture, rice, onion (optional), lettuce and tomatoes.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate before serving.

title: strawberry chews
directions: Grind coconut and almonds in blender until fine.
Add 1 1/2 packages Jell-O, sugar, milk, vanilla and food coloring.
Mix thoroughly and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Shape into strawberry shapes and roll in remaining dry Jell-O.
Make leaves and berries with green frosting.
Yields 100 small berries.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Boil chicken and then cool and chunk.
Mix sour cream and soup in a bowl with chicken.
Place in a baking dish.
Mix stuffing and put on chicken mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice-pork chops
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Place pork chops in baking pan. Sprinkle onion soup mix on top of chops and add rice mixture. Bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours or until tender.

title: crab puffs
directions: Combine crabmeat, green pepper, celery, olives, hot pepper and enough mayonnaise to moisten; mix lightly.
Cut tops from miniature cream puffs.
Fill with mixture.
Replace tops and serve.
Refrigerate remaining.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and oleo.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Add sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, soda and flour.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Bake in a large flat pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and spread topping on hot cake.
