Place under broiler for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle(only takes 9 minutes)
directions: Grease a cookie sheet ahead of time. In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook 8 minutes on High, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook 1 minute longer at High.
Add baking soda and quickly stir until light and foamy.
Immediately pour onto lightly buttered baking sheet.
Spread out thin.
When cool, break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: donna's corn
directions: Soften cream cheese with butter.
Add green chilies and mix well.
Add garlic salt and corn; mix well.
Heat in microwave or 350° in oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: apricot-angel dessert
directions: In a large saucepan, combine apricot nectar, sugar and cornstarch over medium-high heat.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil until thick.

title: chicken cacciatore(country:  italian)
directions: Mix flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Cook chicken over medium heat until brown (approximately 15 minutes on each side).
Drain fat from skillet.

title: roast duck with noodles
directions: Pick, singe and clean the duck.
Rub it with salt.
Fill cavities with noodle dressing.
Truss the duck.
Roast in uncovered pan in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes per pound.

title: tuna rio grande
directions: Melt butter or margarine in square baking dish.
Stir in chili sauce.
Crumble tuna into the chili and margarine.
Top with cheese, then with prepared muffin mix.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Cut into squares.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: caramel dip for apples
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and condensed milk in heavy saucepan.
Cook slowly to soft ball stage (230°).
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Dip apples.
Cool in buttered pan.

title: oat pancakes
directions: In
a
medium
mixing
bowl,
combine
the flour, oats, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Make a well in the center.
In a separate
bowl,
mix
the
milk, eggs, oil and lemon juice. Pour in
dry
ingredients;
stir
just until moistened.
Pour small amounts
of
batter
onto
a lightly oiled hot griddle. When bubbles form on top of pancakes, turn over and cook until other side is golden brown.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in apples, vanilla and nuts.

title: potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes and cool.
Cook bacon (crisp).
In heavy pot melt margarine; add flour.
Add milk and cook 5 to 6 minutes to let it thicken.
Scoop pulp out of potatoes (I chopped my potatoes).
Add cheese and green onions; salt and pepper to taste. On very low heat add sour cream.
When serving add chopped bacon and cheese.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Melt lard in Dutch oven over medium heat. Add flour and stir constantly for 30 to 35 minutes or until dark brown in color. Add onion, bell pepper, garlic and celery to roux.
Mix well and cook 5 minutes.
Slowly stir in chicken broth.
Add spices. Simmer 45 minutes. Add okra, crabmeat, flounder, scallops and shrimp.
Cook 15 minutes longer. Add salt to taste. Serve over cooked rice. Sprinkle gumbo file over top. Serve with hard rolls.
Makes enough for several people while watching Alabama and Auburn play football.
Good food, good friends; who cares who wins the ball game, right?
It is a lot of work and money but worth every bit of it.

title: mama's egg custard
directions: Beat well and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in saucepan large enough to serve as a mixing bowl.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat mixture thoroughly until blended.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Bake in an 11 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 45 minutes or until done. Remove from oven and top with marshmallows.
Return to oven until marshmallows begin to puff up.
Cool and use the following icing.

title: chocolate peanut butter cream pie
directions: Spoon 1/2 cup of the fudge topping into batter of crust. Place in freeze 10 minutes. Whisk peanut butter and milk in a large bowl until well blended. Add pudding mix. Beat for 2 minutes or until smooth. The mixture will be thick. Stir in 1/2 whipped topping. Gently spoon over chocolate layer. Top with remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate 3 hours. Drizzle with 1/4 of fudge topping just before serving.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients in a medium bowl with a hand beater until smooth (for thinner pancakes, stir in 2 to 4 tablespoons additional milk).
Grease a heated griddle if necessary.
(To see if griddle is hot enough, sprinkle with a few drops of water; if bubbles skitter around, heat is just right.)
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup of batter onto the hot griddle.
Cook until pancakes are puffed and dry around edges.
Turn and cook other side until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 pancakes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, Karo syrup and boiling water in a large heavy skillet; bring to a boil.
Add raw peanuts and cook until nuts pop or turn orange color.
Add paraffin.
When it is melted, add soda. Stir until it has puffed up.
Pour at once onto a well buttered baking sheet.
Spread thin to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: mary's bread
directions: In small bowl, dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
In large bowl, mix shortening, salt and sugar.
Add boiling water and stir well.
Add eggs and stir well.
Add flour and yeast mixture alternately to shortening mixture.
Stir well.
Leave in big bowl. Cover with towel.
Set in warm place.
Let rise until double. Punch down.
Roll out on a floured board and knead.
Melt margarine in 2 loaf pans.
Shape dough into loaf and put in pan.
Let rise to top of pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sausage bread
directions: Simmer raisins in water for 10 minutes; drain and reserve liquid.
Stir uncooked sausage into liquid.
Add sugar, flour, spice and soda.
Mix in nuts and raisins.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 3 loaves (9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch).
Serve with cream cheese.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
In double boiler melt chocolate chips with paraffin.
Dip candy balls into chocolate and put on buttered waxed paper.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind zucchini, green peppers and onions.
Add salt and mix well.
Soak overnight and then drain.
Cook turmeric, celery seed, sugar and vinegar until clear.
Pour over relish mixture, then seal in jars.
(I mix the relish mixture and vinegar mixture together and heat thoroughly.)
May put in hot water bath for 5 minutes for sure sealing of jars.

title: oatmeal cocoa cake
directions: Pour boiling water over rolled oats; set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add oat mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and beat in.
Bake in greased 9 x 13
x 2-inch pan at 350° for 39 minutes; dust with powdered sugar or chocolate creme frosting dotted with enough to make it special.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate any meat desired. Delicious!

title: mary's ricotta cheese pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir in noodles, being careful not to break them. Drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
They firm quickly.

title: baked squash
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add salt and squash to sugar mixture.
Scald milk and add to squash mixture.
Fold in eggs and vanilla.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg if desired.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean, approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: steak soup
directions: Lightly brown ground beef.
Set aside.
Combine melted margarine, flour and first 1 quart of water.
Set aside.
In large Dutch oven or pot, combine onions, carrots and celery.
Add second 1 quart of water and boil 5 minutes.
Add browned ground beef and margarine, flour and water mixture to vegetable pot.
Next, add frozen mixed vegetables, tomatoes, Accent, beef bouillon cubes, pepper, salt and sugar.
Bring all to boil, then simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
May sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on surface after soup is ladled into bowls.

title: baked beans
directions: Crumble bacon in beans.
Mix together.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in microwave.

title: chicken and crescent roll casserole
directions: Pour milk, 1/2 cheese and both cans of soup into saucepan; heat, but do not boil.
Roll pieces of chicken into each triangle of crescent rolls toward little end and tuck in.
Place in large glass baking dish.
Pour sauce over top.
Put other cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook sugar, cream, syrup and peanuts over low heat until it reaches 240°.
Add butter, vanilla, powdered sugar and red food coloring. Drop by spoon on waxed paper.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk about 7 minutes until a bit of it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat while cooling pan in sink of cold water until fudge thickens.
Add walnuts if desired.
Keep beating until it holds a form.
Turn onto buttered dinner plate.
When firm, cut into squares.
Makes 24 to 36, depending on size.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Combine over hot (not boiling) water: Nestles Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels and sweetened condensed milk. Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth. Stir in Diamond walnuts and vanilla extract. Spread into foil lined 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm, (about 2 hours). Makes 1 1/4 pounds of fudge.

title: hamburger cornbread casserole
directions: Layer the ingredients in a greased 9 x 13-inch bread pan or large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: freezer jam
directions: Boil tomatoes, pineapple, lemon juice and sugar for 20 minutes.
Pour into jars.
Leave on counter for 24 hours. Refrigerate or freeze.
Double recipe makes 7 pints.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and carrots.
Dice into bite-size.
Chop celery and onion.
Put all ingredients into a deep saucepan; add enough water for mixture to stir easily.
Simmer until all is tender. Great on a cold day served with cornbread.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and salt; add apples and nuts.
Set aside.
Beat eggs with fork; add oil, vanilla and sugar.
Mix with flour mixture.
Turn into well-greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake in 350°
oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin flan(low-fat)
directions: In a heavy skillet, cook the 1 cup sugar over medium-high heat until it begins to melt.
Do not stir; just shake the skillet occasionally.

When the sugar starts to melt, reduce heat to low. Cook, stirring frequently, until the sugar is golden brown. Quickly pour the sugar into a 10-inch deep pie pan or quiche dish. Tilt to evenly coat the bottom.
Place the pie plate or quiche dish in a large roasting pan.
Place on a rack in the oven.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Coat a skillet with butter or margarine and add the hamburger. Allow hamburger to reach room temperature so that you can easily crumble into small bits.
Brown slowly over medium heat.
Add 1/2 cup water, the onions, garlic powder to taste, tomato sauce, the chili powder and the salt.
Simmer over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Use as sauce for hot dogs.

title: mirliton au gratin (or choyote)
directions: Peel and slice mirlitons, saute the slices in skillet in half the butter until lightly browned.
Season slices with seasoned salt to taste, place in baking dish.
In same skillet, saute the onions and garlic in rest of the butter until lightly browned. Add flour, Tabasco and stir for 1 minute.
Add milk and stir until sauce thickens and begins to simmer.
Pour sauce over mirlitons, top with cheese and parsley.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: creamy herb sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Taste and adjust seasonings.
Serve this sauce with grilled or steamed chicken, fish, shrimp or scallops.
Use as a dressing for a chicken and water chestnut salad.

title: cheddar chili tomato pots
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease shallow baking dish.
Cut 1/2-inch slice from top of each tomato; scoop out pulp and seeds, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Invert tomatoes on paper towel and let drain 20 minutes.
Combine 3 cups of the cheese, chilies, oregano and garlic in medium size bowl.
Divide mixture evenly among tomato shells.
Arrange tomato shells in baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onions.
Put in saucepan with tomato sauce, shredded cheese, chili powder, buttermilk and egg.
Warm and mix with ground beef.
Simmer a few minutes.
Line baking dish bottom with a pack of buttermilk biscuits.
Pour in mixture. Put remaining biscuits on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are golden brown.
Use pack of 10 biscuits and pull apart.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill about 2 hours. Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in large pot until they are soft.
Drain water off the potatoes.
Peel warm potatoes.
Mix sweet potatoes, margarine and sugar thoroughly.
Add milk, eggs, extract and nutmeg.
Pour mixture into four unbaked 9-inch pie crust shells. Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: corbet cake
directions: Ignore directions on cake mix box.
Mix all the ingredients except chocolate chips.
Then after it is mixed well, add chips. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° in a Bundt cake pan.

title: toffee
directions: Mix butter, sugars and water.
Bring to a boil (stir constantly) until forms hard crack.
Remove from heat; add soda (work fast).
Add almonds, pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool 5 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips.
As they melt, spread over candy; sprinkle with pecans.

title: carrot hot dish
directions: Melt margarine and stir into flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and let melt.

title: fruit stand pizza
directions: This is a dip done in layers on a pizza pan or something similar.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Place over 1 cup cooked rice in casserole.
Cook until hot throughout.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti in thirds.
Cook as directed on package. Rinse in cold water.
Chop the following ingredients together: cucumbers, green pepper, purple onion and tomatoes.
Mix spaghetti with vegetables.
Add McCormick's salad seasoning.
Stir well. Add about 8 to 12 ounces Zesty Italian dressing.
Refrigerate overnight.
Good for weeks.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine graham crackers and 1/2 cup melted butter or margarine. Spread in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.

title: chicken with caraway seed(kylling med karve)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine flour and potato starch; season with salt and pepper and coat the chicken pieces.
Heat shortening in a heavy skillet; brown the chicken on all sides.
Transfer chicken to a casserole.
Add the caraway seed, broth and 1 cup of sour cream.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Just before serving, stir in the remaining sour cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade caramel corn
directions: Heat all ingredients except baking soda until bubbly around edges.
Cook 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda until foamy.
Pour over popped popcorn and stir to coat well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 200° for 1 hour.

title: brussels sprouts with flair
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine.
Add frozen Brussels sprouts.
Stir in mushrooms, onions, salt and pepper.
Cover and saute 2 minutes.
Uncover and saute 3 minutes longer or until sprouts are crisp-tender, stirring frequently to prevent sticking. Serves 6 to 8.

title: turkey with eggplant
directions: Cover eggplant with boiling
water; let stand 5 minutes and drain well.
Dredge
turkey meat in mixture of cornstarch, soy sauce and sherry.
Heat pan; add oil and saute hot peppers until they turn color.
Remove
from pan.
Saute turkey in the same pan until done.
Add
eggplant,
garlic, sauteed peppers, ginger and soup stock.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook until vegetables are tender.
Mash, leaving some chunks. Add milk, whipping cream and seasonings.
Simmer for a few minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions for 5 minutes. Drain.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, cheese and eggs in bowl. Put broccoli in a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish or casserole. Add soup mixture, spreading evenly over broccoli.
Top with crushed crackers, then dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In double boiler, over simmering water, melt chocolate.
Stir in coconut, salt and almond extract.
Fold egg whites into chocolate mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes until set.
Remove from oven immediately and let cool.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Chill approximately 4 hours in refrigerator.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls into mixture, using a toothpick.
Lay on wax paper.
Store in sealed container.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix as directed
on
cake mix adding pie filling.
Bake in 1 or 2 large greased oblong cake pans.
Make thin layers.

title: tom thumb cookie bars
directions: Combine shortening and salt, add 1/2 cup of brown sugar. Cream thoroughly.
Add 1 cup flour and blend.
Spread mixture in baking pan that is greased.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Add remaining 1 cup of brown sugar and vanilla to the well beaten eggs.
Beat until thick and foamy.
Then add 2 tablespoons flour, baking powder, coconut, nuts and blend.
Spread this over baked mixture.
Return to oven (325°) and bake 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Use 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: kruzckiki(bow ties)
directions: Roll out very thin. Cut into strips, 4 x 1 1/2-inch.
Cut a slit down the center and slip one end through to make it like a bow tie.
Deep fry until golden.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cooled.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the margarine.
Gradually add sugars.
Add beaten eggs. Stir well.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, alternating with applesauce.
Grease and flour bread loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan.

title: sam's skillet feast
directions: Put olive oil in frying pan.
Put cut up potatoes, peppers, mushrooms, garlic and onions in frying pan.
Cook until tender. Beat eggs and put over the mixture until set.

title: dave's deviled potatoes
directions: Wash and cut potatoes into 4 pieces each.
Cover with boiling water.
Add salt and cook for 20 to 40 minutes, until tender when tested with a fork.
Drain.
Add softened butter and warm milk. Mash until free of lumps.
Heat the sour cream in a small saucepan over a low flame.
Add mustard and sugar to the sour cream.
Pour over the potatoes and mix well.
Heat in a 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Fry and drain.
Sprinkle over bottom of unbaked 10-inch pie shell.
Add cheese.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sour cream, parsley, onion soup and spices.
Beat. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack about 10 minutes before serving.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Rinse in cold water and drain. Brown meat.
Add peppers, garlic, onion and tomato sauce.
Simmer slowly for 5 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream and noodles.
Alternate layers of noodles and meat in a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Begin with noodles and finish with meat on top.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 2-quart pan or baking dish.
Combine 1 cup sugar and flour. Add milk and stir until mixed well.
Pour over butter in baking dish, but do not stir. Combine peaches and remaining sugar (1 cup) and spoon over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Fry beef, green pepper and onions.
Drain grease.
Stir in tomato sauce, green beans and salt.
Place canned biscuits on greased baking dish.
Flatten out.
Beat egg and pour over biscuits.
Add 1/2 of egg mixture.
Pour beef mixture over this, then add remaining cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Use at least 2 to 4 kinds of fresh, canned or dried fruit. Make sure fruits have a nice contrast in color, flavor and texture.
Avoid soft or messy fruits.

title: polish hamburgers
directions: Mix together ingredients well in large bowl.
Shape into hamburgers; fry in large skillet on medium flame, for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 burgers.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cream butter, sugar and cream.
Add eggs.
Add flour and sour milk or buttermilk.
Add pumpkin and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done (test with toothpick).

title: oprah's potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes well, leaving skins on and cut them in half. Transfer to large kettle and cover with water.
Heat water to boil. Reduce to a simmer and cook until potatoes are tender, about 25 minutes.

Drain the potatoes well and return to the pot. Do not peel them. Add butter and begin to mash by hand. Add horseradish sauce, cream, salt and pepper. Continue to mash until texture is creamy but still slightly lumpy. Garnish with parsley.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except broccoli and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese and margarine are melted, about 2 minutes.
Add broccoli and salt.
Cook, stirring frequently, until heated, 2 minutes.
Turn in casserole.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in margarine bowl.
Chill at least 2 hours (better overnight) before serving.

title: delia's manhattan clam chowder
directions: Braise onion in butter.
Add celery, carrots, potatoes and a little water; cook 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, thyme, pepper, clam juice and clams.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil and serve.

title: black forest cake
directions: Beat cake mix and pie filling together.
Add the eggs and oil. Grease and flour a Bundt cake pan.
Bake for 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
When cake is completely cool, you may add a can of cherry pie filling over it as a topping.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Beat milk powder into milk until very well blended.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Pour into a heavy saucepan and stirring constantly over low heat, cook 5 minutes.
Cool.
Stir well before using.
Keeps, refrigerated, one week.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water until tender; save broth.
Pick chicken from bone into small pieces.
Melt margarine; pour over dressing mix.
Mix 1 or 1 1/2 cups of chicken broth into the dressing until moist.
In a 2-quart casserole, slightly cover bottom with dressing.
Blend 1/4 can of chicken broth to each can of soup.
Alternate rows of chicken, cream of chicken soup, dressing, chicken and cream of chicken soup.
Sprinkle with remaining dressing.
Bake in moderate oven until soup bubbles up into dressing (20 or 30 minutes).
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: fireside pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat butter and sugars together until fluffy.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt together.
Add to pumpkin mixture and stir to mix well.
Stir in nuts and dates.

title: 3-p salad
directions: Mix dressing of mayonnaise, sugar, and cream.
Put first 3 ingredients into a medium mixing bowl.
Mix lightly.
Add dressing.
Toss lightly.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Serve on leaf lettuce.

title: grandma's fruitcake
directions: Melt butter
and brown sugar.
Add eggs, flour, flavoring and spices.
Cut
and mix fruit and nuts in separate bowl. Add 1/2 cup flour
and mix.
Add crushed pineapple.
Mix fruit in batter. Pour in
prepared pans sprayed with vegetable oil. Bake 1 hour at 200° or 2
hours
at
Makes	4 to 6 loaf pans.

title: butter roll crust
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in water. Roll crust out to 1/8-inch thickness, rectangle.
Cut in half. Sprinkle with sugar.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Roll up into two rolls.

title: onion-mushroom ground beef
directions: Pour half the contents of the canned items into an oven-safe casserole dish.
Put in the ground sirloin and cover it with the rest of contents of the canned items.
Cover dish and cook in the oven at 350° for an hour.
Serve over rice.
It's easy and the leftovers, if you have any, are just as delicious.

title: dill sauce(fish topping)
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika.
Add milk and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Stir in lemon juice and dill weed.

title: peanut caramel chews
directions: Butter a 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine milk and caramels in saucepan.
Heat until melted and stir until smooth.
Combine cereal and peanuts.
Pour melted caramel over cereal mixture, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Press firmly into pan with buttered hands.
Refrigerate until firm.
Then let stand at room temperature about 10 minutes; cut into squares.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 25 squares.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Clean potatoes and bake at 400° for one hour.
Remove from oven and cut slit lengthwise in each potato.
Open about 1/2-inch and carefully scoop out pulp.
Do not tear skin.
Mash pulp in a bowl and add butter, sour cream, salt and pepper; mix well.
Spoon into shells.
Top with cheese.
Return to oven and lightly brown. Remove and top with parsley.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown onion and hamburger in hot shortening.
Add catsup, vinegar and sauce and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Pour over beans; add a little water, if too thick.
Bake in a slow oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add spaghetti.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder, soda and salt. Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually and cream well, then add chocolate and blend.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk; beat after each addition until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Bake in two 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse.
Mix milk and egg together. Add noodles and toss to coat.
Place on the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Mix the spaghetti sauce and ground beef.
Put on top of the noodles (if you like a lot of sauce, use a little more). Top with cheese, then pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ryeta's chicken rice casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 9 1/2 x 11-inch cake pan with lid.
Sprinkle box of rice in bottom of pan.

title: sugar-free date-prune bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly coat a 9 x 13-inch pan with vegetable cooking spray.
In a 2-quart saucepan, bring water to boil.
Add dates, prunes and raisins.
Cook over medium-high heat until water has been absorbed by fruit, 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove fruit from heat.
Stir in margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Mix until eggs are well incorporated and margarine is melted.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spread evenly into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Cream margarine, 1 cup sugar and eggs.
Add lemon rind.
Sift baking powder and flour; add alternately with milk.
Add nuts.

title: microwave mexican manicotti
directions: Combine uncooked ground beef, beans, oregano and cumin; mix well.
Fill uncooked shells with meat mixture.
Arrange in 10 x 6 x 2-inch microwave-safe dish.
Combine water and sauce and pour over shells.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Cook on High 10 minutes (giving dish 1/2 turn once).
Using tongs, turn shells over and cook on Medium 17 to 19 minutes (or adjust to your microwave) until pasta is tender.
Combine sour cream, onion and olives.
Pour down center of casserole and top with cheese.
Cook on High 2 minutes until cheese melts.

title: wendy's italian chili
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and cool 30 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: ground beef-tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with chopped onion.
Drain excess fat.
Divide into 3 portions.
Place a layer of meat in a large casserole dish.
Add a layer of Tater Tots, then add a layer of soup already reconstituted.
Repeat these layers until all ingredients are used.
Save enough Tater Tots to be sure the top is covered for baking.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain pasta.
Brown sausage and drain.
In 3-quart dish mix pasta, sausage and remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake uncovered about 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a jar and refrigerate.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except biscuits.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, then add oil, sour cream and suga and beat well. Stir in zucchini, then stir in combined dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 80 minutes.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add flour and lightly brown it.
Add celery, green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp.
Cover and cook 15 minutes on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add salt, pepper and cayenne to taste.
Add onion tops and parsley.
Simmer a few minutes, covered, to blend seasoning.
Serve over rice.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into balls.
Roll in coconut or powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: baked chicken oriental
directions: Shake fryer in flour, salt and pepper.
Roll in one cube melted oleo.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn chicken and baste several times with sauce of butter, honey, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Bake another 30 minutes.

title: savory turkey loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in a greased baking dish (microwave-safe).
Cook on power 7. Bake for 16 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger until brown.
Put in a baking dish.
Fry the vegetables with the garlic a little.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Add ketchup, salt and pork and beans.
Mix well.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: miner's fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, milk, flour, egg yolk, vanilla, and butter together.
Cook over medium heat until thickens.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat saved egg whites until stiff.
Frost pie and lightly brown frosting.
Yields two 9-inch pies.

title: hot shrimp on spinach
directions: Shell the shrimp and sprinkle with thyme, oregano, tarragon, coriander and pepper.
Place in a single layer in a dish and sprinkle with oil.
Set aside.

title: pecan cream cheese cake
directions: Butter a 2-quart Bundt pan heavily, using 2 tablespoons of butter.
Sprinkle
pan
with
the 1/2 cup of finely chopped nuts, then the 2 tablespoons of sugar; set aside.
Cream 1 cup of butter with
cream cheese and 1 1/2 cups of sugar.
Beat in egg yolks one
at a time until thoroughly blended. Sift flour with
baking powder
and
salt;	gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in	remaining
pecans.
Beat egg whites stiff, then
fold into creamed mixture.
Carefully pour into prepared pan.

title: southwest quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch pie tin or quiche tin with a generous pie crust. Bake in the oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
While it is baking, broil the bacon until crisp and slice the peppers into large pieces and fry gently until limp, but not soft.
Do not burn.
Pieces should be 3/4 by 2-inch.
Grate the Cheddar and mix Cheddar, Ricotta, herbs, pepper flakes and the half and half.
Beat the eggs and add in.
Crumble the bacon, lay it on bottom of crust.
Add 1/3 of the egg and cheese mix, drain and add the peppers and add in the rest of other mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until done.
Let rest15 minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease cookie sheets or line with parchment paper.
In a large bowl, cream together butter, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well with each addition.
Combine flour, baking soda and cinnamon, gradually stir into creamed sugar mixture.
Fold in rolled oats, raisins and pecans.
Drop rounded spoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes in preheated oven.
Remove cookies to wire rack and cool completely.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Combine yeast and warm water.
Dissolve completely.
Add sugar and margarine, then gradually add flour until the consistency of biscuit dough.
Let rise for 30 minutes, then pour out on floured board.
Knead for about 15 minutes.
Make into rolls and put in buttered pan.
Let rise (will take about 15 to 20 minutes if around heat).
Bake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook, debone and shred chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix chicken soup and sour cream and pour over chicken. Melt margarine and add crushed Ritz crackers and poppy seed. Spoon over soup mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: grilled tomatoes
directions: Melt margarine; cut tomatoes in half.
Toss bread crumbs, parsley, garlic, salt, pepper and basil with margarine.
Sprinkle over tomatoes; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.

title: lemon garlic chicken thighs
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken.
Put chicken in a bowl.
Toss thighs with mixture of lemon juice, crushed garlic and thyme.
Make sure all sides are coated.
Refrigerate chicken for 2 hours.
Turn pieces at least once.
Place thighs on rack in baking pan, skin side up.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's famous chocolate cookie dessert
directions: Whip cream with sugar and vanilla until soft peaks hold shape. Carefully open package of cookies, keeping broken cookies together to reassemble later.
In bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan, place 10 to 11 whole cookies.
Place a good teaspoon of whipped cream on each cookie.
Gently press another cookie layer on top of cream, just so cream comes to edge of cookie.
Repeat process of layering until stacks are 3 to 4 cookies high (box should have 47 cookies).
On the top cookie, gently spread spoonful of cream out to edges of cookie.
Cover pan with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, top each with a cherry! (Broken cookies can be reassembled for middle layers.) Serve 1 to 2 per person.

title: ruth's pumpkin stuff(diabetic)
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients well.
Pour into Pam sprayed 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle all the box of cake mix over top.
Drizzle melted margarine and nuts over all.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned peach preserves(these are very good!)
directions: Combine fruit and sugar well.
Let stand 12 to 18 hours in a cool place (I use the refrigerator).
Sterilize canning jars and lids.
Begin cooking peach mixture on medium until boiling.
Stir frequently and be careful not to scorch!
Boil gently until fruit becomes clear and syrup thick.
As mixture thickens, remember to stir frequently to avoid scorching.
Skim off foam if necessary. Pour hot preserves into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Wipe jar rims and put on lids.
Put jars upside-down on a cabinet (out of a draft) for about 30 minutes.
Then set upright and let cool.

title: tomato soup
directions: In large saucepan, bring tomatoes to a boil, then add baking soda and garlic salt.
Reduce heat.
Add the milk.
Heat through but do not boil.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, margarine and vanilla. Form into balls and chill.
Melt chips and paraffin together and dip balls in chip mixture.

title: party punch
directions: The day of the party, mix all ingredients that morning and freeze.
About every hour, stir so that punch keeps a slush consistency.
Serves 25.
Make plenty.
Everyone comes back for seconds.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan; combine milk, flour, sugar and milk with dash of cinnamon.
Pour directly in center of baking pan, in middle of butter.
Add peaches on top; 1 cup juice on peaches.
Sprinkle a little cinnamon.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: turkey and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Heat large nonstick skillet or wok over medium-high heat until hot.
Add oil; heat until it ripples.
Add turkey; cook and stir 4 to 5 minutes or until no longer pink.
Add frozen vegetables and onion; cook and stir 6 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are crisp and tender.
Add stir-fry sauce; cook until thoroughly heated. Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 (1 1/4 cup) servings.

title: recipe for happy day
directions: Blend together with Bible study.
Keep cool and serve generously.

title: pita bread with mediterranean mix
directions: Combine all ingredients except pita bread in a large bowl, mixing to coat with oil.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours. Cut pita bread into halves with scissors.
Pull open to form pockets.
Fill with chilled mixture.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes to partially thaw.
Stir in rice, chicken, soup, milk, half the cheese and onion.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bailey irish cream
directions: Brew extra strong coffee, allowing 3 tablespoons of coffee for each 6 ounces water (1 1/2 times usual strength).
Chill until serving time.
Pour over ice cubes in a tall glass; pass favorite spirits and a bottle of Amaretto for flavoring.
Top with whipped cream.

title: quick chocolate sour cream cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together the brown sugar, sour cream and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and beat well.
Turn into a 5 x 9-inch greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched in center.

title: cajun orange roughy
directions: Bake orange roughy at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Depends on how thick your fillets are.
Pour off any juices in pan.
Coat the fish with Cajun style barbecue sauce.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Turn fish over, coat the other side with barbecue sauce and return to oven for 5 minutes.
Keep repeating, until fish is easily flaked with a fork.

title: mother's fried pies
directions: Mix dry ingredients with Crisco.
Mix egg and Pet milk with mixer.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight.
Roll out and cut, using a small saucer.
Add Wilderness pie fruit of choice by teaspoon and fold over.
Press around the edge with a fork. Fry in deep fat until brown.

title: peppermint hot chocolate
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, stir Nestle Quik and milk until smooth. Over medium heat, heat mixture to boiling.
Stir in peppermint candy.
Heat until tiny bubbles form around edge of pan.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour into cups or mugs; top with marshmallows.
We use a coffee grinder to crush the peppermint candy to powder.
Then candy melts a lot faster.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Divide 1/4 of mixture into another bowl and add beer or 7-Up until it becomes a runny batter.
Dip fish into dry mixture, then into liquid batter, then deposit into deep-fryer until golden brown.

title: wedding party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, three (6-ounce) cans of water, orange juice and sugar together.
Set aside to chill.
Add 1 quart of ice water and ginger ale to mixture to serve.
Add ice cream to top.
Stir lightly.
Yields 20 servings.

title: moc shu
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Scrape corn off ears
in 3 layers. Add remaining ingredients.
Turn fire down low and cook for 2 hours.
Stir often.
You may use 1 can of Ro-Tel tomatoes instead of 2 tomatoes for spicy Moc Shu.

title: alese's coconut sheet cake
directions: Mix cake by package directions. Boil milk, sugar and 1/2 of coconut for 10 minutes in saucepan.
As soon as cake is out of the oven, pierce the whole top with a fork.
Pour boiled mixture over the cake and let cool.
Fold remaining coconut into Cool Whip and spread on top of the cooled cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken crescent wraps
directions: Separate crescent rolls and place a small amount of diced chicken in center of each roll.
Roll up and tuck sides in.
Place the 8 chicken wraps in a baking dish.
Heat all other ingredients in a saucepan.
Pour over the wraps.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes until wraps are brown.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Put cornbread mix in a large bowl; add milk and stir.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Bake in 3 greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans at 400° for about 35 minutes until done.
This freezes well.

title: green salad
directions: Mix the lime Jell-O and hot water together and cool.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Add the cooled Jell-O.
Add pineapple, marshmallows, Cool Whip and nuts.
Put in square pan. Cool at least 2 hours.

title: mocha nut freeze
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and nuts in a medium bowl.
Add melted butter and mix.
Sprinkle 2 cups crumb mixture in buttered 9-inch square baking dish and press firmly.
Freeze. Put evaporated milk in a medium bowl and freeze until ice crystals form around edges of bowl.
Beat egg whites and salt until frothy. Slowly beat in remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Whip evaporated milk until stiff and add cocoa and coffee.
Fold into meringue.
Spread over frozen crumb mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture and freeze several hours.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs and oil; stir until ingredients are moist (do not beat).
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour in 3 greased round cake pans and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Start
oven
minutes
before
baking. Bake at 350°. Wash, but do not peel.
Cut out
deep core from stem end.
Cut core; remove core and discard.
Then
chop
the
rest of core. Sprinkle salt and pepper into the hollowed out tomatoes.

title: easy strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar.
Let stand overnight. Boil 15 minutes. Add Jell-O.
Cool and store in refrigerator.

title: fresh lemon poppy seed dip
directions: Mix well and chill several hours before serving.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix the flour, 2/3 cup sugar and salt.
Gradually add milk. Cook in double boiler or on low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add small amount of hot mixture to beaten egg yolks. Stir into remaining hot mixture.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Cool.
Add butter and vanilla extract.
Pour into baked pie shell and spread with meringue made of egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Brown veal lightly in 4 tablespoons butter.
Season to taste. Saute mushrooms and onion in casserole dish (2-quart) with rest of butter for 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, water, beef broth and wine.
Bring to boil.
Pour over meat; cover.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy with few grains of sugar, using high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Lower the speed to folding, or low.
Add sifted flour alternately with whipping cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavor.
Pour in prepared pan (one greased with Crisco) and dust with flour.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° (use small pan of water in stove for moisture).
Allow to cool in pan before removing cake from pan.

title: health salad
directions: Mix orange jello and boiling water together and let stand. Mix all remaining ingredients with set jello.
Decorate with miniature marshmallows.
